8514 
8515 void HexagonABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
8516  unsigned RegsLeft = 6;
8517  if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
8518  FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
8519  for (auto &I : FI.arguments())
8520  I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type, &RegsLeft);
8521 }
8522 
8523 static bool HexagonAdjustRegsLeft(uint64_t Size, unsigned *RegsLeft) {
8524  assert(Size <= 64 && "Not expecting to pass arguments larger than 64 bits"
8525  " through registers");
8526 
8527  if (*RegsLeft == 0)
8528  return false;
8529 
8530  if (Size <= 32) {
8531  (*RegsLeft)--;
8532  return true;
8533  }
8534 
8535  if (2 <= (*RegsLeft & (~1U))) {
8536  *RegsLeft = (*RegsLeft & (~1U)) - 2;
8537  return true;
8538  }
8539 
8540  // Next available register was r5 but candidate was greater than 32-bits so it
8541  // has to go on the stack. However we still consume r5
8542  if (*RegsLeft == 1)
8543  *RegsLeft = 0;
8544 
8545  return false;
8546 }
8547 
8548 ABIArgInfo HexagonABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty,
8549  unsigned *RegsLeft) const {
8550  if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
8551  // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
8552  if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
8553  Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
8554 
8555  uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
8556  if (Size <= 64)
8557  HexagonAdjustRegsLeft(Size, RegsLeft);
8558 
8559  if (Size > 64 && Ty->isBitIntType())
8560  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/true);
8561 
8562  return isPromotableIntegerTypeForABI(Ty) ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty)
8563  : ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
8564  }
8565 
8566  if (CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI()))
8567  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
8568 
8569  // Ignore empty records.
8570  if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
8571  return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
8572 
8573  uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
8574  unsigned Align = getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty);
8575 
8576  if (Size > 64)
8577  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/true);
8578 
8579  if (HexagonAdjustRegsLeft(Size, RegsLeft))
8580  Align = Size <= 32 ? 32 : 64;
8581  if (Size <= Align) {
8582  // Pass in the smallest viable integer type.
8583  if (!llvm::isPowerOf2_64(Size))
8584  Size = llvm::NextPowerOf2(Size);
8585  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getIntNTy(getVMContext(), Size));
8586  }
8587  return DefaultABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(Ty);
8588 }
8589 
8590 ABIArgInfo HexagonABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
8591  if (RetTy->isVoidType())
8592  return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
8593 
8594  const TargetInfo &T = CGT.getTarget();
8595  uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy);
8596 
8597  if (RetTy->getAs<VectorType>()) {
8598  // HVX vectors are returned in vector registers or register pairs.
8599  if (T.hasFeature("hvx")) {
8600  assert(T.hasFeature("hvx-length64b") || T.hasFeature("hvx-length128b"));
8601  uint64_t VecSize = T.hasFeature("hvx-length64b") ? 64*8 : 128*8;
8602  if (Size == VecSize || Size == 2*VecSize)
8603  return ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg();
8604  }
8605  // Large vector types should be returned via memory.
8606  if (Size > 64)
8607  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy);
8608  }
8609 
8610  if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(RetTy)) {
8611  // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
8612  if (const EnumType *EnumTy = RetTy->getAs<EnumType>())
8613  RetTy = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
8614 
8615  if (Size > 64 && RetTy->isBitIntType())
8616  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy, /*ByVal=*/false);
8617 
8618  return isPromotableIntegerTypeForABI(RetTy) ? ABIArgInfo::getExtend(RetTy)
8619  : ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
8620  }
8621 
8622  if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), RetTy, true))
8623  return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
8624 
8625  // Aggregates <= 8 bytes are returned in registers, other aggregates
8626  // are returned indirectly.
8627  if (Size <= 64) {
8628  // Return in the smallest viable integer type.
8629  if (!llvm::isPowerOf2_64(Size))
8630  Size = llvm::NextPowerOf2(Size);
8631  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getIntNTy(getVMContext(), Size));
8632  }
8633  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(RetTy, /*ByVal=*/true);
8634 }
8635 
8636 Address HexagonABIInfo::EmitVAArgFromMemory(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
8637  Address VAListAddr,
8638  QualType Ty) const {
8639  // Load the overflow area pointer.
8640  Address __overflow_area_pointer_p =
8641  CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAListAddr, 2, "__overflow_area_pointer_p");
8642  llvm::Value *__overflow_area_pointer = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(
8643  __overflow_area_pointer_p, "__overflow_area_pointer");
8644 
8645  uint64_t Align = CGF.getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty) / 8;
8646  if (Align > 4) {
8647  // Alignment should be a power of 2.
8648  assert((Align & (Align - 1)) == 0 && "Alignment is not power of 2!");
8649 
8650  // overflow_arg_area = (overflow_arg_area + align - 1) & -align;
8651  llvm::Value *Offset = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int64Ty, Align - 1);
8652 
8653  // Add offset to the current pointer to access the argument.
8654  __overflow_area_pointer =
8655  CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, __overflow_area_pointer, Offset);
8656  llvm::Value *AsInt =
8657  CGF.Builder.CreatePtrToInt(__overflow_area_pointer, CGF.Int32Ty);
8658 
8659  // Create a mask which should be "AND"ed
8660  // with (overflow_arg_area + align - 1)
8661  llvm::Value *Mask = llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, -(int)Align);
8662  __overflow_area_pointer = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(
8663  CGF.Builder.CreateAnd(AsInt, Mask), __overflow_area_pointer->getType(),
8664  "__overflow_area_pointer.align");
8665  }
8666 
8667  // Get the type of the argument from memory and bitcast
8668  // overflow area pointer to the argument type.
8669  llvm::Type *PTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Ty);
8670  Address AddrTyped = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(
8671  Address(__overflow_area_pointer, CGF.Int8Ty,
8672  CharUnits::fromQuantity(Align)),
8673  PTy);
8674 
8675  // Round up to the minimum stack alignment for varargs which is 4 bytes.
8676  uint64_t Offset = llvm::alignTo(CGF.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) / 8, 4);
8677 
8678  __overflow_area_pointer = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(
8679  CGF.Int8Ty, __overflow_area_pointer,
8680  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, Offset),
8681  "__overflow_area_pointer.next");
8682  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(__overflow_area_pointer, __overflow_area_pointer_p);
8683 
8684  return AddrTyped;
8685 }
8686 
8687 Address HexagonABIInfo::EmitVAArgForHexagon(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
8688  Address VAListAddr,
8689  QualType Ty) const {
8690  // FIXME: Need to handle alignment
8691  llvm::Type *BP = CGF.Int8PtrTy;
8692  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
8693  Address VAListAddrAsBPP = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(VAListAddr, BP, "ap");
8694  llvm::Value *Addr = Builder.CreateLoad(VAListAddrAsBPP, "ap.cur");
8695  // Handle address alignment for type alignment > 32 bits
8696  uint64_t TyAlign = CGF.getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty) / 8;
8697  if (TyAlign > 4) {
8698  assert((TyAlign & (TyAlign - 1)) == 0 && "Alignment is not power of 2!");
8699  llvm::Value *AddrAsInt = Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Addr, CGF.Int32Ty);
8700  AddrAsInt = Builder.CreateAdd(AddrAsInt, Builder.getInt32(TyAlign - 1));
8701  AddrAsInt = Builder.CreateAnd(AddrAsInt, Builder.getInt32(~(TyAlign - 1)));
8702  Addr = Builder.CreateIntToPtr(AddrAsInt, BP);
8703  }
8704  Address AddrTyped = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(
8705  Address(Addr, CGF.Int8Ty, CharUnits::fromQuantity(TyAlign)),
8706  CGF.ConvertType(Ty));
8707 
8708  uint64_t Offset = llvm::alignTo(CGF.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) / 8, 4);
8709  llvm::Value *NextAddr = Builder.CreateGEP(
8710  CGF.Int8Ty, Addr, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, Offset), "ap.next");
8711  Builder.CreateStore(NextAddr, VAListAddrAsBPP);
8712 
8713  return AddrTyped;
8714 }
8715 
8716 Address HexagonABIInfo::EmitVAArgForHexagonLinux(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
8717  Address VAListAddr,
8718  QualType Ty) const {
8719  int ArgSize = CGF.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) / 8;
8720 
8721  if (ArgSize > 8)
8722  return EmitVAArgFromMemory(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty);
8723 
8724  // Here we have check if the argument is in register area or
8725  // in overflow area.
8726  // If the saved register area pointer + argsize rounded up to alignment >
8727  // saved register area end pointer, argument is in overflow area.
8728  unsigned RegsLeft = 6;
8729  Ty = CGF.getContext().getCanonicalType(Ty);
8730  (void)classifyArgumentType(Ty, &RegsLeft);
8731 
8732  llvm::BasicBlock *MaybeRegBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("vaarg.maybe_reg");
8733  llvm::BasicBlock *InRegBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("vaarg.in_reg");
8734  llvm::BasicBlock *OnStackBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("vaarg.on_stack");
8735  llvm::BasicBlock *ContBlock = CGF.createBasicBlock("vaarg.end");
8736 
8737  // Get rounded size of the argument.GCC does not allow vararg of
8738  // size < 4 bytes. We follow the same logic here.
8739  ArgSize = (CGF.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) <= 32) ? 4 : 8;
8740  int ArgAlign = (CGF.getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) <= 32) ? 4 : 8;
8741 
8742  // Argument may be in saved register area
8743  CGF.EmitBlock(MaybeRegBlock);
8744 
8745  // Load the current saved register area pointer.
8746  Address __current_saved_reg_area_pointer_p = CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(
8747  VAListAddr, 0, "__current_saved_reg_area_pointer_p");
8748  llvm::Value *__current_saved_reg_area_pointer = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(
8749  __current_saved_reg_area_pointer_p, "__current_saved_reg_area_pointer");
8750 
8751  // Load the saved register area end pointer.
8752  Address __saved_reg_area_end_pointer_p = CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(
8753  VAListAddr, 1, "__saved_reg_area_end_pointer_p");
8754  llvm::Value *__saved_reg_area_end_pointer = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(
8755  __saved_reg_area_end_pointer_p, "__saved_reg_area_end_pointer");
8756 
8757  // If the size of argument is > 4 bytes, check if the stack
8758  // location is aligned to 8 bytes
8759  if (ArgAlign > 4) {
8760 
8761  llvm::Value *__current_saved_reg_area_pointer_int =
8762  CGF.Builder.CreatePtrToInt(__current_saved_reg_area_pointer,
8763  CGF.Int32Ty);
8764 
8765  __current_saved_reg_area_pointer_int = CGF.Builder.CreateAdd(
8766  __current_saved_reg_area_pointer_int,
8767  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, (ArgAlign - 1)),
8768  "align_current_saved_reg_area_pointer");
8769 
8770  __current_saved_reg_area_pointer_int =
8771  CGF.Builder.CreateAnd(__current_saved_reg_area_pointer_int,
8772  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, -ArgAlign),
8773  "align_current_saved_reg_area_pointer");
8774 
8775  __current_saved_reg_area_pointer =
8776  CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(__current_saved_reg_area_pointer_int,
8777  __current_saved_reg_area_pointer->getType(),
8778  "align_current_saved_reg_area_pointer");
8779  }
8780 
8781  llvm::Value *__new_saved_reg_area_pointer =
8782  CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, __current_saved_reg_area_pointer,
8783  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, ArgSize),
8784  "__new_saved_reg_area_pointer");
8785 
8786  llvm::Value *UsingStack = nullptr;
8787  UsingStack = CGF.Builder.CreateICmpSGT(__new_saved_reg_area_pointer,
8788  __saved_reg_area_end_pointer);
8789 
8790  CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(UsingStack, OnStackBlock, InRegBlock);
8791 
8792  // Argument in saved register area
8793  // Implement the block where argument is in register saved area
8794  CGF.EmitBlock(InRegBlock);
8795 
8796  llvm::Type *PTy = CGF.ConvertType(Ty);
8797  llvm::Value *__saved_reg_area_p = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(
8798  __current_saved_reg_area_pointer, llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(PTy));
8799 
8800  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(__new_saved_reg_area_pointer,
8801  __current_saved_reg_area_pointer_p);
8802 
8803  CGF.EmitBranch(ContBlock);
8804 
8805  // Argument in overflow area
8806  // Implement the block where the argument is in overflow area.
8807  CGF.EmitBlock(OnStackBlock);
8808 
8809  // Load the overflow area pointer
8810  Address __overflow_area_pointer_p =
8811  CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(VAListAddr, 2, "__overflow_area_pointer_p");
8812  llvm::Value *__overflow_area_pointer = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(
8813  __overflow_area_pointer_p, "__overflow_area_pointer");
8814 
8815  // Align the overflow area pointer according to the alignment of the argument
8816  if (ArgAlign > 4) {
8817  llvm::Value *__overflow_area_pointer_int =
8818  CGF.Builder.CreatePtrToInt(__overflow_area_pointer, CGF.Int32Ty);
8819 
8820  __overflow_area_pointer_int =
8821  CGF.Builder.CreateAdd(__overflow_area_pointer_int,
8822  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, ArgAlign - 1),
8823  "align_overflow_area_pointer");
8824 
8825  __overflow_area_pointer_int =
8826  CGF.Builder.CreateAnd(__overflow_area_pointer_int,
8827  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, -ArgAlign),
8828  "align_overflow_area_pointer");
8829 
8830  __overflow_area_pointer = CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(
8831  __overflow_area_pointer_int, __overflow_area_pointer->getType(),
8832  "align_overflow_area_pointer");
8833  }
8834 
8835  // Get the pointer for next argument in overflow area and store it
8836  // to overflow area pointer.
8837  llvm::Value *__new_overflow_area_pointer = CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(
8838  CGF.Int8Ty, __overflow_area_pointer,
8839  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, ArgSize),
8840  "__overflow_area_pointer.next");
8841 
8842  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(__new_overflow_area_pointer,
8843  __overflow_area_pointer_p);
8844 
8845  CGF.Builder.CreateStore(__new_overflow_area_pointer,
8846  __current_saved_reg_area_pointer_p);
8847 
8848  // Bitcast the overflow area pointer to the type of argument.
8849  llvm::Type *OverflowPTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Ty);
8850  llvm::Value *__overflow_area_p = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(
8851  __overflow_area_pointer, llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(OverflowPTy));
8852 
8853  CGF.EmitBranch(ContBlock);
8854 
8855  // Get the correct pointer to load the variable argument
8856  // Implement the ContBlock
8857  CGF.EmitBlock(ContBlock);
8858 
8859  llvm::Type *MemTy = CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Ty);
8860  llvm::Type *MemPTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(MemTy);
8861  llvm::PHINode *ArgAddr = CGF.Builder.CreatePHI(MemPTy, 2, "vaarg.addr");
8862  ArgAddr->addIncoming(__saved_reg_area_p, InRegBlock);
8863  ArgAddr->addIncoming(__overflow_area_p, OnStackBlock);
8864 
8865  return Address(ArgAddr, MemTy, CharUnits::fromQuantity(ArgAlign));
8866 }
8867 
8868 Address HexagonABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
8869  QualType Ty) const {
8870 
8871  if (getTarget().getTriple().isMusl())
8872  return EmitVAArgForHexagonLinux(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty);
8873 
8874  return EmitVAArgForHexagon(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty);
8875 }

8877 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8878 // Lanai ABI Implementation
8879 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8880 
8881 namespace {
8882 class LanaiABIInfo : public DefaultABIInfo {
8883 public:
8884  LanaiABIInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT) : DefaultABIInfo(CGT) {}
8885 
8886  bool shouldUseInReg(QualType Ty, CCState &State) const;
8887 
8888  void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override {
8889  CCState State(FI);
8890  // Lanai uses 4 registers to pass arguments unless the function has the
8891  // regparm attribute set.
8892  if (FI.getHasRegParm()) {
8893  State.FreeRegs = FI.getRegParm();
8894  } else {
8895  State.FreeRegs = 4;
8896  }
8897 
8898  if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
8899  FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
8900  for (auto &I : FI.arguments())
8901  I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type, State);
8902  }
8903 
8904  ABIArgInfo getIndirectResult(QualType Ty, bool ByVal, CCState &State) const;
8905  ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType RetTy, CCState &State) const;
8906 };
8907 } // end anonymous namespace
8908 
8909 bool LanaiABIInfo::shouldUseInReg(QualType Ty, CCState &State) const {
8910  unsigned Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
8911  unsigned SizeInRegs = llvm::alignTo(Size, 32U) / 32U;
8912 
8913  if (SizeInRegs == 0)
8914  return false;
8915 
8916  if (SizeInRegs > State.FreeRegs) {
8917  State.FreeRegs = 0;
8918  return false;
8919  }
8920 
8921  State.FreeRegs -= SizeInRegs;
8922 
8923  return true;
8924 }
8925 
8926 ABIArgInfo LanaiABIInfo::getIndirectResult(QualType Ty, bool ByVal,
8927  CCState &State) const {
8928  if (!ByVal) {
8929  if (State.FreeRegs) {
8930  --State.FreeRegs; // Non-byval indirects just use one pointer.
8931  return getNaturalAlignIndirectInReg(Ty);
8932  }
8933  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, false);
8934  }
8935 
8936  // Compute the byval alignment.
8937  const unsigned MinABIStackAlignInBytes = 4;
8938  unsigned TypeAlign = getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty) / 8;
8939  return ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(CharUnits::fromQuantity(4), /*ByVal=*/true,
8940  /*Realign=*/TypeAlign >
8941  MinABIStackAlignInBytes);
8942 }
8943 
8944 ABIArgInfo LanaiABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty,
8945  CCState &State) const {
8946  // Check with the C++ ABI first.
8947  const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>();
8948  if (RT) {
8949  CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(RT, getCXXABI());
8950  if (RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_Indirect) {
8951  return getIndirectResult(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false, State);
8952  } else if (RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory) {
8953  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/true);
8954  }
8955  }
8956 
8957  if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
8958  // Structures with flexible arrays are always indirect.
8959  if (RT && RT->getDecl()->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
8960  return getIndirectResult(Ty, /*ByVal=*/true, State);
8961 
8962  // Ignore empty structs/unions.
8963  if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
8964  return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
8965 
8966  llvm::LLVMContext &LLVMContext = getVMContext();
8967  unsigned SizeInRegs = (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) + 31) / 32;
8968  if (SizeInRegs <= State.FreeRegs) {
8969  llvm::IntegerType *Int32 = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(LLVMContext);
8970  SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 3> Elements(SizeInRegs, Int32);
8971  llvm::Type *Result = llvm::StructType::get(LLVMContext, Elements);
8972  State.FreeRegs -= SizeInRegs;
8973  return ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg(Result);
8974  } else {
8975  State.FreeRegs = 0;
8976  }
8977  return getIndirectResult(Ty, true, State);
8978  }
8979 
8980  // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
8981  if (const auto *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
8982  Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
8983 
8984  bool InReg = shouldUseInReg(Ty, State);
8985 
8986  // Don't pass >64 bit integers in registers.
8987  if (const auto *EIT = Ty->getAs<BitIntType>())
8988  if (EIT->getNumBits() > 64)
8989  return getIndirectResult(Ty, /*ByVal=*/true, State);
8990 
8991  if (isPromotableIntegerTypeForABI(Ty)) {
8992  if (InReg)
8993  return ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg();
8994  return ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty);
8995  }
8996  if (InReg)
8997  return ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg();
8998  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
8999 }
9000

9003 public:
9004  LanaiTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT)
9005  : TargetCodeGenInfo(std::make_unique<LanaiABIInfo>(CGT)) {}
9006 };
9007 }

9009 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9010 // AMDGPU ABI Implementation
9011 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

9013 namespace {
9014 
9015 class AMDGPUABIInfo final : public DefaultABIInfo {
9016 private:
9017  static const unsigned MaxNumRegsForArgsRet = 16;
9018 
9019  unsigned numRegsForType(QualType Ty) const;
9020 
9021  bool isHomogeneousAggregateBaseType(QualType Ty) const override;
9022  bool isHomogeneousAggregateSmallEnough(const Type *Base,
9023  uint64_t Members) const override;
9024 
9025  // Coerce HIP scalar pointer arguments from generic pointers to global ones.
9026  llvm::Type *coerceKernelArgumentType(llvm::Type *Ty, unsigned FromAS,
9027  unsigned ToAS) const {
9028  // Single value types.
9029  auto *PtrTy = llvm::dyn_cast<llvm::PointerType>(Ty);
9030  if (PtrTy && PtrTy->getAddressSpace() == FromAS)
9031  return llvm::PointerType::getWithSamePointeeType(PtrTy, ToAS);
9032  return Ty;
9033  }
9034 
9035 public:
9036  explicit AMDGPUABIInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT) :
9037  DefaultABIInfo(CGT) {}
9038 
9039  ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
9040  ABIArgInfo classifyKernelArgumentType(QualType Ty) const;
9041  ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty, unsigned &NumRegsLeft) const;
9042 
9043  void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
9044  Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
9045  QualType Ty) const override;
9046 };
9047 
9048 bool AMDGPUABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregateBaseType(QualType Ty) const {
9049  return true;
9050 }
9051 
9052 bool AMDGPUABIInfo::isHomogeneousAggregateSmallEnough(
9053  const Type *Base, uint64_t Members) const {
9054  uint32_t NumRegs = (getContext().getTypeSize(Base) + 31) / 32;
9055 
9056  // Homogeneous Aggregates may occupy at most 16 registers.
9057  return Members * NumRegs <= MaxNumRegsForArgsRet;
9058 }
9059 
9060 /// Estimate number of registers the type will use when passed in registers.
9061 unsigned AMDGPUABIInfo::numRegsForType(QualType Ty) const {
9062  unsigned NumRegs = 0;
9063 
9064  if (const VectorType *VT = Ty->getAs<VectorType>()) {
9065  // Compute from the number of elements. The reported size is based on the
9066  // in-memory size, which includes the padding 4th element for 3-vectors.
9067  QualType EltTy = VT->getElementType();
9068  unsigned EltSize = getContext().getTypeSize(EltTy);
9069 
9070  // 16-bit element vectors should be passed as packed.
9071  if (EltSize == 16)
9072  return (VT->getNumElements() + 1) / 2;
9073 
9074  unsigned EltNumRegs = (EltSize + 31) / 32;
9075  return EltNumRegs * VT->getNumElements();
9076  }
9077 
9078  if (const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>()) {
9079  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
9080  assert(!RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember());
9081 
9082  for (const FieldDecl *Field : RD->fields()) {
9083  QualType FieldTy = Field->getType();
9084  NumRegs += numRegsForType(FieldTy);
9085  }
9086 
9087  return NumRegs;
9088  }
9089 
9090  return (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) + 31) / 32;
9091 }
9092 
9093 void AMDGPUABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
9094  llvm::CallingConv::ID CC = FI.getCallingConvention();
9095 
9096  if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
9097  FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
9098 
9099  unsigned NumRegsLeft = MaxNumRegsForArgsRet;
9100  for (auto &Arg : FI.arguments()) {
9101  if (CC == llvm::CallingConv::AMDGPU_KERNEL) {
9102  Arg.info = classifyKernelArgumentType(Arg.type);
9103  } else {
9104  Arg.info = classifyArgumentType(Arg.type, NumRegsLeft);
9105  }
9106  }
9107 }
9108 
9109 Address AMDGPUABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
9110  QualType Ty) const {
9111  llvm_unreachable("AMDGPU does not support varargs");
9112 }
9113 
9114 ABIArgInfo AMDGPUABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
9115  if (isAggregateTypeForABI(RetTy)) {
9116  // Records with non-trivial destructors/copy-constructors should not be
9117  // returned by value.
9118  if (!getRecordArgABI(RetTy, getCXXABI())) {
9119  // Ignore empty structs/unions.
9120  if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), RetTy, true))
9121  return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
9122 
9123  // Lower single-element structs to just return a regular value.
9124  if (const Type *SeltTy = isSingleElementStruct(RetTy, getContext()))
9125  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CGT.ConvertType(QualType(SeltTy, 0)));
9126 
9127  if (const RecordType *RT = RetTy->getAs<RecordType>()) {
9128  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
9129  if (RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
9130  return DefaultABIInfo::classifyReturnType(RetTy);
9131  }
9132 
9133  // Pack aggregates <= 4 bytes into single VGPR or pair.
9134  uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy);
9135  if (Size <= 16)
9136  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(getVMContext()));
9137 
9138  if (Size <= 32)
9139  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()));
9140 
9141  if (Size <= 64) {
9142  llvm::Type *I32Ty = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext());
9143  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::ArrayType::get(I32Ty, 2));
9144  }
9145 
9146  if (numRegsForType(RetTy) <= MaxNumRegsForArgsRet)
9147  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
9148  }
9149  }
9150 
9151  // Otherwise just do the default thing.
9152  return DefaultABIInfo::classifyReturnType(RetTy);
9153 }
9154 
9155 /// For kernels all parameters are really passed in a special buffer. It doesn't
9156 /// make sense to pass anything byval, so everything must be direct.
9157 ABIArgInfo AMDGPUABIInfo::classifyKernelArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
9158  Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
9159 
9160  // TODO: Can we omit empty structs?
9161 
9162  if (const Type *SeltTy = isSingleElementStruct(Ty, getContext()))
9163  Ty = QualType(SeltTy, 0);
9164 
9165  llvm::Type *OrigLTy = CGT.ConvertType(Ty);
9166  llvm::Type *LTy = OrigLTy;
9167  if (getContext().getLangOpts().HIP) {
9168  LTy = coerceKernelArgumentType(
9169  OrigLTy, /*FromAS=*/getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default),
9170  /*ToAS=*/getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::cuda_device));
9171  }
9172 
9173  // FIXME: Should also use this for OpenCL, but it requires addressing the
9174  // problem of kernels being called.
9175  //
9176  // FIXME: This doesn't apply the optimization of coercing pointers in structs
9177  // to global address space when using byref. This would require implementing a
9178  // new kind of coercion of the in-memory type when for indirect arguments.
9179  if (!getContext().getLangOpts().OpenCL && LTy == OrigLTy &&
9180  isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
9181  return ABIArgInfo::getIndirectAliased(
9182  getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty),
9183  getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_constant),
9184  false /*Realign*/, nullptr /*Padding*/);
9185  }
9186 
9187  // If we set CanBeFlattened to true, CodeGen will expand the struct to its
9188  // individual elements, which confuses the Clover OpenCL backend; therefore we
9189  // have to set it to false here. Other args of getDirect() are just defaults.
9190  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(LTy, 0, nullptr, false);
9191 }
9192 
9193 ABIArgInfo AMDGPUABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty,
9194  unsigned &NumRegsLeft) const {
9195  assert(NumRegsLeft <= MaxNumRegsForArgsRet && "register estimate underflow");
9196 
9197  Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
9198 
9199  if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
9200  // Records with non-trivial destructors/copy-constructors should not be
9201  // passed by value.
9202  if (auto RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI()))
9203  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
9204 
9205  // Ignore empty structs/unions.
9206  if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
9207  return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
9208 
9209  // Lower single-element structs to just pass a regular value. TODO: We
9210  // could do reasonable-size multiple-element structs too, using getExpand(),
9211  // though watch out for things like bitfields.
9212  if (const Type *SeltTy = isSingleElementStruct(Ty, getContext()))
9213  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CGT.ConvertType(QualType(SeltTy, 0)));
9214 
9215  if (const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>()) {
9216  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
9217  if (RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
9218  return DefaultABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(Ty);
9219  }
9220 
9221  // Pack aggregates <= 8 bytes into single VGPR or pair.
9222  uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
9223  if (Size <= 64) {
9224  unsigned NumRegs = (Size + 31) / 32;
9225  NumRegsLeft -= std::min(NumRegsLeft, NumRegs);
9226 
9227  if (Size <= 16)
9228  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(getVMContext()));
9229 
9230  if (Size <= 32)
9231  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()));
9232 
9233  // XXX: Should this be i64 instead, and should the limit increase?
9234  llvm::Type *I32Ty = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext());
9235  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::ArrayType::get(I32Ty, 2));
9236  }
9237 
9238  if (NumRegsLeft > 0) {
9239  unsigned NumRegs = numRegsForType(Ty);
9240  if (NumRegsLeft >= NumRegs) {
9241  NumRegsLeft -= NumRegs;
9242  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
9243  }
9244  }
9245  }
9246 
9247  // Otherwise just do the default thing.
9248  ABIArgInfo ArgInfo = DefaultABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(Ty);
9249  if (!ArgInfo.isIndirect()) {
9250  unsigned NumRegs = numRegsForType(Ty);
9251  NumRegsLeft -= std::min(NumRegs, NumRegsLeft);
9252  }
9253 
9254  return ArgInfo;
9255 }

9290 
9291 static bool requiresAMDGPUProtectedVisibility(const Decl *D,
9292  llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
9293  if (GV->getVisibility() != llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility)
9294  return false;
9295 
9296  return D->hasAttr<OpenCLKernelAttr>() ||
9297  (isa<FunctionDecl>(D) && D->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>()) ||
9298  (isa<VarDecl>(D) &&
9299  (D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>() || D->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>() ||
9300  cast<VarDecl>(D)->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinSurfaceType() ||
9301  cast<VarDecl>(D)->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinTextureType()));
9302 }
9303 
9304 void AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::setFunctionDeclAttributes(
9305  const FunctionDecl *FD, llvm::Function *F, CodeGenModule &M) const {
9306  const auto *ReqdWGS =
9307  M.getLangOpts().OpenCL ? FD->getAttr<ReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>() : nullptr;
9308  const bool IsOpenCLKernel =
9309  M.getLangOpts().OpenCL && FD->hasAttr<OpenCLKernelAttr>();
9310  const bool IsHIPKernel = M.getLangOpts().HIP && FD->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>();
9311 
9312  const auto *FlatWGS = FD->getAttr<AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr>();
9313  if (ReqdWGS || FlatWGS) {
9314  unsigned Min = 0;
9315  unsigned Max = 0;
9316  unsigned XDim = 0;
9317  unsigned YDim = 0;
9318  unsigned ZDim = 0;
9319  ASTContext &Ctx = M.getContext();
9320  if (FlatWGS) {
9321  Min = FlatWGS->getMin()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(Ctx).getExtValue();
9322  Max = FlatWGS->getMax()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(Ctx).getExtValue();
9323  }
9324  if (ReqdWGS) {
9325  XDim = ReqdWGS->getXDimVal()->getZExtValue();
9326  YDim = ReqdWGS->getYDimVal()->getZExtValue();
9327  ZDim = ReqdWGS->getZDimVal()->getZExtValue();
9328  }
9329  if (ReqdWGS && Min == 0 && Max == 0)
9330  Min = Max = XDim * YDim * ZDim;
9331 
9332  if (Min != 0) {
9333  assert(Min <= Max && "Min must be less than or equal Max");
9334 
9335  std::string AttrVal = llvm::utostr(Min) + "," + llvm::utostr(Max);
9336  F->addFnAttr("amdgpu-flat-work-group-size", AttrVal);
9337  } else
9338  assert(Max == 0 && "Max must be zero");
9339  } else if (IsOpenCLKernel || IsHIPKernel) {
9340  // By default, restrict the maximum size to a value specified by
9341  // --gpu-max-threads-per-block=n or its default value for HIP.
9342  const unsigned OpenCLDefaultMaxWorkGroupSize = 256;
9343  const unsigned DefaultMaxWorkGroupSize =
9344  IsOpenCLKernel ? OpenCLDefaultMaxWorkGroupSize
9345  : M.getLangOpts().GPUMaxThreadsPerBlock;
9346  std::string AttrVal =
9347  std::string("1,") + llvm::utostr(DefaultMaxWorkGroupSize);
9348  F->addFnAttr("amdgpu-flat-work-group-size", AttrVal);
9349  }
9350 
9351  if (const auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<AMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr>()) {
9352  unsigned Min =
9353  Attr->getMin()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(M.getContext()).getExtValue();
9354  unsigned Max = Attr->getMax() ? Attr->getMax()
9355  ->EvaluateKnownConstInt(M.getContext())
9356  .getExtValue()
9357  : 0;
9358 
9359  if (Min != 0) {
9360  assert((Max == 0 || Min <= Max) && "Min must be less than or equal Max");
9361 
9362  std::string AttrVal = llvm::utostr(Min);
9363  if (Max != 0)
9364  AttrVal = AttrVal + "," + llvm::utostr(Max);
9365  F->addFnAttr("amdgpu-waves-per-eu", AttrVal);
9366  } else
9367  assert(Max == 0 && "Max must be zero");
9368  }
9369 
9370  if (const auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<AMDGPUNumSGPRAttr>()) {
9371  unsigned NumSGPR = Attr->getNumSGPR();
9372 
9373  if (NumSGPR != 0)
9374  F->addFnAttr("amdgpu-num-sgpr", llvm::utostr(NumSGPR));
9375  }
9376 
9377  if (const auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<AMDGPUNumVGPRAttr>()) {
9378  uint32_t NumVGPR = Attr->getNumVGPR();
9379 
9380  if (NumVGPR != 0)
9381  F->addFnAttr("amdgpu-num-vgpr", llvm::utostr(NumVGPR));
9382  }
9383 }
9384 
9385 void AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::setTargetAttributes(
9386  const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV, CodeGen::CodeGenModule &M) const {
9387  if (requiresAMDGPUProtectedVisibility(D, GV)) {
9388  GV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::ProtectedVisibility);
9389  GV->setDSOLocal(true);
9390  }
9391 
9392  if (GV->isDeclaration())
9393  return;
9394 
9395  llvm::Function *F = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
9396  if (!F)
9397  return;
9398 
9399  const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D);
9400  if (FD)
9401  setFunctionDeclAttributes(FD, F, M);
9402 
9403  const bool IsHIPKernel =
9404  M.getLangOpts().HIP && FD && FD->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>();
9405 
9406  if (IsHIPKernel)
9407  F->addFnAttr("uniform-work-group-size", "true");
9408 
9409  if (M.getContext().getTargetInfo().allowAMDGPUUnsafeFPAtomics())
9410  F->addFnAttr("amdgpu-unsafe-fp-atomics", "true");
9411 
9412  if (!getABIInfo().getCodeGenOpts().EmitIEEENaNCompliantInsts)
9413  F->addFnAttr("amdgpu-ieee", "false");
9414 }
9415 
9416 unsigned AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::getOpenCLKernelCallingConv() const {
9417  return llvm::CallingConv::AMDGPU_KERNEL;
9418 }
9419 
9420 // Currently LLVM assumes null pointers always have value 0,
9421 // which results in incorrectly transformed IR. Therefore, instead of
9422 // emitting null pointers in private and local address spaces, a null
9423 // pointer in generic address space is emitted which is casted to a
9424 // pointer in local or private address space.
9425 llvm::Constant *AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::getNullPointer(
9426  const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM, llvm::PointerType *PT,
9427  QualType QT) const {
9428  if (CGM.getContext().getTargetNullPointerValue(QT) == 0)
9429  return llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(PT);
9430 
9431  auto &Ctx = CGM.getContext();
9432  auto NPT = llvm::PointerType::getWithSamePointeeType(
9433  PT, Ctx.getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_generic));
9434  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getAddrSpaceCast(
9435  llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(NPT), PT);
9436 }
9437 
9438 LangAS
9439 AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::getGlobalVarAddressSpace(CodeGenModule &CGM,
9440  const VarDecl *D) const {
9441  assert(!CGM.getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
9442  !(CGM.getLangOpts().CUDA && CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) &&
9443  "Address space agnostic languages only");
9444  LangAS DefaultGlobalAS = getLangASFromTargetAS(
9445  CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_global));
9446  if (!D)
9447  return DefaultGlobalAS;
9448 
9449  LangAS AddrSpace = D->getType().getAddressSpace();
9450  assert(AddrSpace == LangAS::Default || isTargetAddressSpace(AddrSpace));
9451  if (AddrSpace != LangAS::Default)
9452  return AddrSpace;
9453 
9454  // Only promote to address space 4 if VarDecl has constant initialization.
9455  if (CGM.isTypeConstant(D->getType(), false) &&
9456  D->hasConstantInitialization()) {
9457  if (auto ConstAS = CGM.getTarget().getConstantAddressSpace())
9458  return ConstAS.getValue();
9459  }
9460  return DefaultGlobalAS;
9461 }
9462 
9463 llvm::SyncScope::ID
9464 AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::getLLVMSyncScopeID(const LangOptions &LangOpts,
9465  SyncScope Scope,
9466  llvm::AtomicOrdering Ordering,
9467  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx) const {
9468  std::string Name;
9469  switch (Scope) {
9470  case SyncScope::HIPSingleThread:
9471  Name = "singlethread";
9472  break;
9473  case SyncScope::HIPWavefront:
9474  case SyncScope::OpenCLSubGroup:
9475  Name = "wavefront";
9476  break;
9477  case SyncScope::HIPWorkgroup:
9478  case SyncScope::OpenCLWorkGroup:
9479  Name = "workgroup";
9480  break;
9481  case SyncScope::HIPAgent:
9482  case SyncScope::OpenCLDevice:
9483  Name = "agent";
9484  break;
9485  case SyncScope::HIPSystem:
9486  case SyncScope::OpenCLAllSVMDevices:
9487  Name = "";
9488  break;
9489  }
9490 
9491  if (Ordering != llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent) {
9492  if (!Name.empty())
9493  Name = Twine(Twine(Name) + Twine("-")).str();
9494 
9495  Name = Twine(Twine(Name) + Twine("one-as")).str();
9496  }
9497 
9498  return Ctx.getOrInsertSyncScopeID(Name);
9499 }
9500 
9501 bool AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::shouldEmitStaticExternCAliases() const {
9502  return false;
9503 }
9504 
9505 void AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::setCUDAKernelCallingConvention(
9506  const FunctionType *&FT) const {
9507  FT = getABIInfo().getContext().adjustFunctionType(
9508  FT, FT->getExtInfo().withCallingConv(CC_OpenCLKernel));
9509 }

9511 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9512 // SPARC v8 ABI Implementation.
9513 // Based on the SPARC Compliance Definition version 2.4.1.
9514 //
9515 // Ensures that complex values are passed in registers.
9516 //
9517 namespace {
9518 class SparcV8ABIInfo : public DefaultABIInfo {
9519 public:

9533  }

9546 namespace {
9547 class SparcV8TargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
9548 public:
9549  SparcV8TargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT)
9550  : TargetCodeGenInfo(std::make_unique<SparcV8ABIInfo>(CGT)) {}
9551 
9552  llvm::Value *decodeReturnAddress(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
9553  llvm::Value *Address) const override {
9554  int Offset;
9555  if (isAggregateTypeForABI(CGF.CurFnInfo->getReturnType()))
9556  Offset = 12;
9557  else
9558  Offset = 8;
9559  return CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, Address,
9560  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, Offset));
9561  }
9562 
9563  llvm::Value *encodeReturnAddress(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
9564  llvm::Value *Address) const override {
9565  int Offset;
9566  if (isAggregateTypeForABI(CGF.CurFnInfo->getReturnType()))
9567  Offset = -12;
9568  else
9569  Offset = -8;
9570  return CGF.Builder.CreateGEP(CGF.Int8Ty, Address,
9571  llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int32Ty, Offset));
9572  }
9573 };

9576 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9577 // SPARC v9 ABI Implementation.
9578 // Based on the SPARC Compliance Definition version 2.4.1.
9579 //
9580 // Function arguments a mapped to a nominal "parameter array" and promoted to
9581 // registers depending on their type. Each argument occupies 8 or 16 bytes in
9582 // the array, structs larger than 16 bytes are passed indirectly.
9583 //
9584 // One case requires special care:
9585 //
9586 // struct mixed {
9587 // int i;
9588 // float f;
9589 // };
9590 //
9591 // When a struct mixed is passed by value, it only occupies 8 bytes in the
9592 // parameter array, but the int is passed in an integer register, and the float
9593 // is passed in a floating point register. This is represented as two arguments
9594 // with the LLVM IR inreg attribute:
9595 //
9596 // declare void f(i32 inreg %i, float inreg %f)
9597 //
9598 // The code generator will only allocate 4 bytes from the parameter array for
9599 // the inreg arguments. All other arguments are allocated a multiple of 8
9600 // bytes.
9601 //
9602 namespace {
9603 class SparcV9ABIInfo : public ABIInfo {
9604 public:
9605  SparcV9ABIInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT) : ABIInfo(CGT) {}
9606 
9607 private:
9608  ABIArgInfo classifyType(QualType RetTy, unsigned SizeLimit) const;
9609  void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
9610  Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
9611  QualType Ty) const override;
9612 
9613  // Coercion type builder for structs passed in registers. The coercion type
9614  // serves two purposes:
9615  //
9616  // 1. Pad structs to a multiple of 64 bits, so they are passed 'left-aligned'
9617  // in registers.
9618  // 2. Expose aligned floating point elements as first-level elements, so the
9619  // code generator knows to pass them in floating point registers.
9620  //
9621  // We also compute the InReg flag which indicates that the struct contains
9622  // aligned 32-bit floats.
9623  //
9624  struct CoerceBuilder {
9625  llvm::LLVMContext &Context;
9626  const llvm::DataLayout &DL;
9627  SmallVector<llvm::Type*, 8> Elems;
9628  uint64_t Size;
9629  bool InReg;
9630 
9631  CoerceBuilder(llvm::LLVMContext &c, const llvm::DataLayout &dl)
9632  : Context(c), DL(dl), Size(0), InReg(false) {}
9633 
9634  // Pad Elems with integers until Size is ToSize.
9635  void pad(uint64_t ToSize) {
9636  assert(ToSize >= Size && "Cannot remove elements");
9637  if (ToSize == Size)
9638  return;
9639 
9640  // Finish the current 64-bit word.
9641  uint64_t Aligned = llvm::alignTo(Size, 64);
9642  if (Aligned > Size && Aligned <= ToSize) {
9643  Elems.push_back(llvm::IntegerType::get(Context, Aligned - Size));
9644  Size = Aligned;
9645  }
9646 
9647  // Add whole 64-bit words.
9648  while (Size + 64 <= ToSize) {
9649  Elems.push_back(llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(Context));
9650  Size += 64;
9651  }
9652 
9653  // Final in-word padding.
9654  if (Size < ToSize) {
9655  Elems.push_back(llvm::IntegerType::get(Context, ToSize - Size));
9656  Size = ToSize;
9657  }
9658  }
9659 
9660  // Add a floating point element at Offset.
9661  void addFloat(uint64_t Offset, llvm::Type *Ty, unsigned Bits) {
9662  // Unaligned floats are treated as integers.
9663  if (Offset % Bits)
9664  return;
9665  // The InReg flag is only required if there are any floats < 64 bits.
9666  if (Bits < 64)
9667  InReg = true;
9668  pad(Offset);
9669  Elems.push_back(Ty);
9670  Size = Offset + Bits;
9671  }
9672 
9673  // Add a struct type to the coercion type, starting at Offset (in bits).
9674  void addStruct(uint64_t Offset, llvm::StructType *StrTy) {
9675  const llvm::StructLayout *Layout = DL.getStructLayout(StrTy);
9676  for (unsigned i = 0, e = StrTy->getNumElements(); i != e; ++i) {
9677  llvm::Type *ElemTy = StrTy->getElementType(i);
9678  uint64_t ElemOffset = Offset + Layout->getElementOffsetInBits(i);
9679  switch (ElemTy->getTypeID()) {
9680  case llvm::Type::StructTyID:
9681  addStruct(ElemOffset, cast<llvm::StructType>(ElemTy));
9682  break;
9683  case llvm::Type::FloatTyID:
9684  addFloat(ElemOffset, ElemTy, 32);
9685  break;
9686  case llvm::Type::DoubleTyID:
9687  addFloat(ElemOffset, ElemTy, 64);
9688  break;
9689  case llvm::Type::FP128TyID:
9690  addFloat(ElemOffset, ElemTy, 128);
9691  break;
9692  case llvm::Type::PointerTyID:
9693  if (ElemOffset % 64 == 0) {
9694  pad(ElemOffset);
9695  Elems.push_back(ElemTy);
9696  Size += 64;
9697  }
9698  break;
9699  default:
9700  break;
9701  }
9702  }
9703  }
9704 
9705  // Check if Ty is a usable substitute for the coercion type.
9706  bool isUsableType(llvm::StructType *Ty) const {
9707  return llvm::makeArrayRef(Elems) == Ty->elements();
9708  }
9709 
9710  // Get the coercion type as a literal struct type.
9711  llvm::Type *getType() const {
9712  if (Elems.size() == 1)
9713  return Elems.front();
9714  else
9715  return llvm::StructType::get(Context, Elems);
9716  }
9717  };
9718 };
9719 } // end anonymous namespace
9720 
9721 ABIArgInfo
9722 SparcV9ABIInfo::classifyType(QualType Ty, unsigned SizeLimit) const {
9723  if (Ty->isVoidType())
9724  return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
9725 
9726  uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
9727 
9728  // Anything too big to fit in registers is passed with an explicit indirect
9729  // pointer / sret pointer.
9730  if (Size > SizeLimit)
9731  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false);
9732 
9733  // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
9734  if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
9735  Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
9736 
9737  // Integer types smaller than a register are extended.
9738  if (Size < 64 && Ty->isIntegerType())
9739  return ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty);
9740 
9741  if (const auto *EIT = Ty->getAs<BitIntType>())
9742  if (EIT->getNumBits() < 64)
9743  return ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty);
9744 
9745  // Other non-aggregates go in registers.
9746  if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty))
9747  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
9748 
9749  // If a C++ object has either a non-trivial copy constructor or a non-trivial
9750  // destructor, it is passed with an explicit indirect pointer / sret pointer.
9751  if (CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI()))
9752  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
9753 
9754  // This is a small aggregate type that should be passed in registers.
9755  // Build a coercion type from the LLVM struct type.
9756  llvm::StructType *StrTy = dyn_cast<llvm::StructType>(CGT.ConvertType(Ty));
9757  if (!StrTy)
9758  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
9759 
9760  CoerceBuilder CB(getVMContext(), getDataLayout());
9761  CB.addStruct(0, StrTy);
9762  CB.pad(llvm::alignTo(CB.DL.getTypeSizeInBits(StrTy), 64));
9763 
9764  // Try to use the original type for coercion.
9765  llvm::Type *CoerceTy = CB.isUsableType(StrTy) ? StrTy : CB.getType();
9766 
9767  if (CB.InReg)
9768  return ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg(CoerceTy);
9769  else
9770  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CoerceTy);
9771 }
9772 
9773 Address SparcV9ABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
9774  QualType Ty) const {
9775  ABIArgInfo AI = classifyType(Ty, 16 * 8);
9776  llvm::Type *ArgTy = CGT.ConvertType(Ty);
9777  if (AI.canHaveCoerceToType() && !AI.getCoerceToType())
9778  AI.setCoerceToType(ArgTy);
9779 
9780  CharUnits SlotSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(8);
9781 
9782  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
9783  Address Addr = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(VAListAddr, "ap.cur"),
9784  getVAListElementType(CGF), SlotSize);
9785  llvm::Type *ArgPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(ArgTy);
9786 
9787  auto TypeInfo = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty);
9788 
9789  Address ArgAddr = Address::invalid();
9790  CharUnits Stride;
9791  switch (AI.getKind()) {
9792  case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
9793  case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand:
9794  case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
9795  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported ABI kind for va_arg");
9796 
9797  case ABIArgInfo::Extend: {
9798  Stride = SlotSize;
9799  CharUnits Offset = SlotSize - TypeInfo.Width;
9800  ArgAddr = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(Addr, Offset, "extend");
9801  break;
9802  }
9803 
9804  case ABIArgInfo::Direct: {
9805  auto AllocSize = getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(AI.getCoerceToType());
9806  Stride = CharUnits::fromQuantity(AllocSize).alignTo(SlotSize);
9807  ArgAddr = Addr;
9808  break;
9809  }
9810 
9811  case ABIArgInfo::Indirect:
9812  case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased:
9813  Stride = SlotSize;
9814  ArgAddr = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, ArgPtrTy, "indirect");
9815  ArgAddr = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(ArgAddr, "indirect.arg"), ArgTy,
9816  TypeInfo.Align);
9817  break;
9818 
9819  case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
9820  return Address(llvm::UndefValue::get(ArgPtrTy), ArgTy, TypeInfo.Align);
9821  }
9822 
9823  // Update VAList.
9824  Address NextPtr = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(Addr, Stride, "ap.next");
9825  Builder.CreateStore(NextPtr.getPointer(), VAListAddr);
9826 
9827  return Builder.CreateElementBitCast(ArgAddr, ArgTy, "arg.addr");
9828 }
9829 
9830 void SparcV9ABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
9831  FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyType(FI.getReturnType(), 32 * 8);
9832  for (auto &I : FI.arguments())
9833  I.info = classifyType(I.type, 16 * 8);
9834 }

9862 
9863 bool
9864 SparcV9TargetCodeGenInfo::initDwarfEHRegSizeTable(CodeGen::CodeGenFunction &CGF,
9865  llvm::Value *Address) const {
9866  // This is calculated from the LLVM and GCC tables and verified
9867  // against gcc output. AFAIK all ABIs use the same encoding.
9868 
9869  CodeGen::CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
9870 
9871  llvm::IntegerType *i8 = CGF.Int8Ty;
9872  llvm::Value *Four8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(i8, 4);
9873  llvm::Value *Eight8 = llvm::ConstantInt::get(i8, 8);
9874 
9875  // 0-31: the 8-byte general-purpose registers
9876  AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Eight8, 0, 31);
9877 
9878  // 32-63: f0-31, the 4-byte floating-point registers
9879  AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Four8, 32, 63);
9880 
9881  // Y = 64
9882  // PSR = 65
9883  // WIM = 66
9884  // TBR = 67
9885  // PC = 68
9886  // NPC = 69
9887  // FSR = 70
9888  // CSR = 71
9889  AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Eight8, 64, 71);
9890 
9891  // 72-87: d0-15, the 8-byte floating-point registers
9892  AssignToArrayRange(Builder, Address, Eight8, 72, 87);
9893 
9894  return false;
9895 }

9897 // ARC ABI implementation.
9898 namespace {
9899 
9900 class ARCABIInfo : public DefaultABIInfo {
9901 public:
9902  using DefaultABIInfo::DefaultABIInfo;
9903 
9904 private:
9905  Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
9906  QualType Ty) const override;
9907 
9908  void updateState(const ABIArgInfo &Info, QualType Ty, CCState &State) const {
9909  if (!State.FreeRegs)
9910  return;
9911  if (Info.isIndirect() && Info.getInReg())
9912  State.FreeRegs--;
9913  else if (Info.isDirect() && Info.getInReg()) {
9914  unsigned sz = (getContext().getTypeSize(Ty) + 31) / 32;
9915  if (sz < State.FreeRegs)
9916  State.FreeRegs -= sz;
9917  else
9918  State.FreeRegs = 0;
9919  }
9920  }
9921 
9922  void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override {
9923  CCState State(FI);
9924  // ARC uses 8 registers to pass arguments.
9925  State.FreeRegs = 8;
9926 
9927  if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
9928  FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
9929  updateState(FI.getReturnInfo(), FI.getReturnType(), State);
9930  for (auto &I : FI.arguments()) {
9931  I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type, State.FreeRegs);
9932  updateState(I.info, I.type, State);
9933  }
9934  }
9935 
9936  ABIArgInfo getIndirectByRef(QualType Ty, bool HasFreeRegs) const;
9937  ABIArgInfo getIndirectByValue(QualType Ty) const;
9938  ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty, uint8_t FreeRegs) const;
9939  ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
9940 };
9941 
9942 class ARCTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
9943 public:
9944  ARCTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT)
9945  : TargetCodeGenInfo(std::make_unique<ARCABIInfo>(CGT)) {}
9946 };
9947 
9948 
9949 ABIArgInfo ARCABIInfo::getIndirectByRef(QualType Ty, bool HasFreeRegs) const {
9950  return HasFreeRegs ? getNaturalAlignIndirectInReg(Ty) :
9951  getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, false);
9952 }
9953 
9954 ABIArgInfo ARCABIInfo::getIndirectByValue(QualType Ty) const {
9955  // Compute the byval alignment.
9956  const unsigned MinABIStackAlignInBytes = 4;
9957  unsigned TypeAlign = getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty) / 8;
9958  return ABIArgInfo::getIndirect(CharUnits::fromQuantity(4), /*ByVal=*/true,
9959  TypeAlign > MinABIStackAlignInBytes);
9960 }
9961 
9962 Address ARCABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
9963  QualType Ty) const {
9964  return emitVoidPtrVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, /*indirect*/ false,
9965  getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty),
9966  CharUnits::fromQuantity(4), true);
9967 }
9968 
9969 ABIArgInfo ARCABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty,
9970  uint8_t FreeRegs) const {
9971  // Handle the generic C++ ABI.
9972  const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>();
9973  if (RT) {
9974  CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(RT, getCXXABI());
9975  if (RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_Indirect)
9976  return getIndirectByRef(Ty, FreeRegs > 0);
9977 
9978  if (RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory)
9979  return getIndirectByValue(Ty);
9980  }
9981 
9982  // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
9983  if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
9984  Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
9985 
9986  auto SizeInRegs = llvm::alignTo(getContext().getTypeSize(Ty), 32) / 32;
9987 
9988  if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
9989  // Structures with flexible arrays are always indirect.
9990  if (RT && RT->getDecl()->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
9991  return getIndirectByValue(Ty);
9992 
9993  // Ignore empty structs/unions.
9994  if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
9995  return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
9996 
9997  llvm::LLVMContext &LLVMContext = getVMContext();
9998 
9999  llvm::IntegerType *Int32 = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(LLVMContext);
10000  SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 3> Elements(SizeInRegs, Int32);
10001  llvm::Type *Result = llvm::StructType::get(LLVMContext, Elements);
10002 
10003  return FreeRegs >= SizeInRegs ?
10004  ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg(Result) :
10005  ABIArgInfo::getDirect(Result, 0, nullptr, false);
10006  }
10007 
10008  if (const auto *EIT = Ty->getAs<BitIntType>())
10009  if (EIT->getNumBits() > 64)
10010  return getIndirectByValue(Ty);
10011 
10012  return isPromotableIntegerTypeForABI(Ty)
10013  ? (FreeRegs >= SizeInRegs ? ABIArgInfo::getExtendInReg(Ty)
10014  : ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty))
10015  : (FreeRegs >= SizeInRegs ? ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg()
10016  : ABIArgInfo::getDirect());
10017 }
10018 
10019 ABIArgInfo ARCABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
10020  if (RetTy->isAnyComplexType())
10021  return ABIArgInfo::getDirectInReg();
10022 
10023  // Arguments of size > 4 registers are indirect.
10024  auto RetSize = llvm::alignTo(getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy), 32) / 32;
10025  if (RetSize > 4)
10026  return getIndirectByRef(RetTy, /*HasFreeRegs*/ true);
10027 
10028  return DefaultABIInfo::classifyReturnType(RetTy);
10029 }
10030 
10031 } // End anonymous namespace.

10033 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
10034 // XCore ABI Implementation
10035 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
10036 
10037 namespace {
10038 
10039 /// A SmallStringEnc instance is used to build up the TypeString by passing
10040 /// it by reference between functions that append to it.
10041 typedef llvm::SmallString<128> SmallStringEnc;
10042 
10043 /// TypeStringCache caches the meta encodings of Types.
10044 ///
10045 /// The reason for caching TypeStrings is two fold:
10046 /// 1. To cache a type's encoding for later uses;
10047 /// 2. As a means to break recursive member type inclusion.
10048 ///
10049 /// A cache Entry can have a Status of:
10050 /// NonRecursive: The type encoding is not recursive;
10051 /// Recursive: The type encoding is recursive;
10052 /// Incomplete: An incomplete TypeString;
10053 /// IncompleteUsed: An incomplete TypeString that has been used in a
10054 /// Recursive type encoding.
10055 ///
10056 /// A NonRecursive entry will have all of its sub-members expanded as fully
10057 /// as possible. Whilst it may contain types which are recursive, the type
10058 /// itself is not recursive and thus its encoding may be safely used whenever
10059 /// the type is encountered.
10060 ///
10061 /// A Recursive entry will have all of its sub-members expanded as fully as
10062 /// possible. The type itself is recursive and it may contain other types which
10063 /// are recursive. The Recursive encoding must not be used during the expansion
10064 /// of a recursive type's recursive branch. For simplicity the code uses
10065 /// IncompleteCount to reject all usage of Recursive encodings for member types.
10066 ///
10067 /// An Incomplete entry is always a RecordType and only encodes its
10068 /// identifier e.g. "s(S){}". Incomplete 'StubEnc' entries are ephemeral and
10069 /// are placed into the cache during type expansion as a means to identify and
10070 /// handle recursive inclusion of types as sub-members. If there is recursion
10071 /// the entry becomes IncompleteUsed.
10072 ///
10073 /// During the expansion of a RecordType's members:
10074 ///
10075 /// If the cache contains a NonRecursive encoding for the member type, the
10076 /// cached encoding is used;
10077 ///
10078 /// If the cache contains a Recursive encoding for the member type, the
10079 /// cached encoding is 'Swapped' out, as it may be incorrect, and...
10080 ///
10081 /// If the member is a RecordType, an Incomplete encoding is placed into the
10082 /// cache to break potential recursive inclusion of itself as a sub-member;
10083 ///
10084 /// Once a member RecordType has been expanded, its temporary incomplete
10085 /// entry is removed from the cache. If a Recursive encoding was swapped out
10086 /// it is swapped back in;
10087 ///
10088 /// If an incomplete entry is used to expand a sub-member, the incomplete
10089 /// entry is marked as IncompleteUsed. The cache keeps count of how many
10090 /// IncompleteUsed entries it currently contains in IncompleteUsedCount;
10091 ///
10092 /// If a member's encoding is found to be a NonRecursive or Recursive viz:
10093 /// IncompleteUsedCount==0, the member's encoding is added to the cache.
10094 /// Else the member is part of a recursive type and thus the recursion has
10095 /// been exited too soon for the encoding to be correct for the member.
10096 ///
10097 class TypeStringCache {
10098  enum Status {NonRecursive, Recursive, Incomplete, IncompleteUsed};
10099  struct Entry {
10100  std::string Str; // The encoded TypeString for the type.
10101  enum Status State; // Information about the encoding in 'Str'.
10102  std::string Swapped; // A temporary place holder for a Recursive encoding
10103  // during the expansion of RecordType's members.
10104  };
10105  std::map<const IdentifierInfo *, struct Entry> Map;
10106  unsigned IncompleteCount; // Number of Incomplete entries in the Map.
10107  unsigned IncompleteUsedCount; // Number of IncompleteUsed entries in the Map.
10108 public:
10109  TypeStringCache() : IncompleteCount(0), IncompleteUsedCount(0) {}
10110  void addIncomplete(const IdentifierInfo *ID, std::string StubEnc);
10111  bool removeIncomplete(const IdentifierInfo *ID);
10112  void addIfComplete(const IdentifierInfo *ID, StringRef Str,
10113  bool IsRecursive);
10114  StringRef lookupStr(const IdentifierInfo *ID);
10115 };
10116 
10117 /// TypeString encodings for enum & union fields must be order.
10118 /// FieldEncoding is a helper for this ordering process.
10119 class FieldEncoding {
10120  bool HasName;
10121  std::string Enc;
10122 public:
10123  FieldEncoding(bool b, SmallStringEnc &e) : HasName(b), Enc(e.c_str()) {}
10124  StringRef str() { return Enc; }
10125  bool operator<(const FieldEncoding &rhs) const {
10126  if (HasName != rhs.HasName) return HasName;
10127  return Enc < rhs.Enc;
10128  }
10129 };
10130

10134  Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
10135  QualType Ty) const override;
10136 };

10152 
10153 // TODO: this implementation is likely now redundant with the default
10154 // EmitVAArg.
10155 Address XCoreABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
10156  QualType Ty) const {
10157  CGBuilderTy &Builder = CGF.Builder;
10158 
10159  // Get the VAList.
10160  CharUnits SlotSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(4);
10161  Address AP = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(VAListAddr),
10162  getVAListElementType(CGF), SlotSize);
10163 
10164  // Handle the argument.
10165  ABIArgInfo AI = classifyArgumentType(Ty);
10166  CharUnits TypeAlign = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(Ty);
10167  llvm::Type *ArgTy = CGT.ConvertType(Ty);
10168  if (AI.canHaveCoerceToType() && !AI.getCoerceToType())
10169  AI.setCoerceToType(ArgTy);
10170  llvm::Type *ArgPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(ArgTy);
10171 
10172  Address Val = Address::invalid();
10173  CharUnits ArgSize = CharUnits::Zero();
10174  switch (AI.getKind()) {
10175  case ABIArgInfo::Expand:
10176  case ABIArgInfo::CoerceAndExpand:
10177  case ABIArgInfo::InAlloca:
10178  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported ABI kind for va_arg");
10179  case ABIArgInfo::Ignore:
10180  Val = Address(llvm::UndefValue::get(ArgPtrTy), ArgTy, TypeAlign);
10181  ArgSize = CharUnits::Zero();
10182  break;
10183  case ABIArgInfo::Extend:
10184  case ABIArgInfo::Direct:
10185  Val = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(AP, ArgTy);
10186  ArgSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(
10187  getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(AI.getCoerceToType()));
10188  ArgSize = ArgSize.alignTo(SlotSize);
10189  break;
10190  case ABIArgInfo::Indirect:
10191  case ABIArgInfo::IndirectAliased:
10192  Val = Builder.CreateElementBitCast(AP, ArgPtrTy);
10193  Val = Address(Builder.CreateLoad(Val), ArgTy, TypeAlign);
10194  ArgSize = SlotSize;
10195  break;
10196  }
10197 
10198  // Increment the VAList.
10199  if (!ArgSize.isZero()) {
10200  Address APN = Builder.CreateConstInBoundsByteGEP(AP, ArgSize);
10201  Builder.CreateStore(APN.getPointer(), VAListAddr);
10202  }
10203 
10204  return Val;
10205 }
10206 
10207 /// During the expansion of a RecordType, an incomplete TypeString is placed
10208 /// into the cache as a means to identify and break recursion.
10209 /// If there is a Recursive encoding in the cache, it is swapped out and will
10210 /// be reinserted by removeIncomplete().
10211 /// All other types of encoding should have been used rather than arriving here.
10212 void TypeStringCache::addIncomplete(const IdentifierInfo *ID,
10213  std::string StubEnc) {
10214  if (!ID)
10215  return;
10216  Entry &E = Map[ID];
10217  assert( (E.Str.empty() || E.State == Recursive) &&
10218  "Incorrectly use of addIncomplete");
10219  assert(!StubEnc.empty() && "Passing an empty string to addIncomplete()");
10220  E.Swapped.swap(E.Str); // swap out the Recursive
10221  E.Str.swap(StubEnc);
10222  E.State = Incomplete;
10223  ++IncompleteCount;
10224 }
10225 
10226 /// Once the RecordType has been expanded, the temporary incomplete TypeString
10227 /// must be removed from the cache.
10228 /// If a Recursive was swapped out by addIncomplete(), it will be replaced.
10229 /// Returns true if the RecordType was defined recursively.
10230 bool TypeStringCache::removeIncomplete(const IdentifierInfo *ID) {
10231  if (!ID)
10232  return false;
10233  auto I = Map.find(ID);
10234  assert(I != Map.end() && "Entry not present");
10235  Entry &E = I->second;
10236  assert( (E.State == Incomplete ||
10237  E.State == IncompleteUsed) &&
10238  "Entry must be an incomplete type");
10239  bool IsRecursive = false;
10240  if (E.State == IncompleteUsed) {
10241  // We made use of our Incomplete encoding, thus we are recursive.
10242  IsRecursive = true;
10243  --IncompleteUsedCount;
10244  }
10245  if (E.Swapped.empty())
10246  Map.erase(I);
10247  else {
10248  // Swap the Recursive back.
10249  E.Swapped.swap(E.Str);
10250  E.Swapped.clear();
10251  E.State = Recursive;
10252  }
10253  --IncompleteCount;
10254  return IsRecursive;
10255 }
10256 
10257 /// Add the encoded TypeString to the cache only if it is NonRecursive or
10258 /// Recursive (viz: all sub-members were expanded as fully as possible).
10259 void TypeStringCache::addIfComplete(const IdentifierInfo *ID, StringRef Str,
10260  bool IsRecursive) {
10261  if (!ID || IncompleteUsedCount)
10262  return; // No key or it is is an incomplete sub-type so don't add.
10263  Entry &E = Map[ID];
10264  if (IsRecursive && !E.Str.empty()) {
10265  assert(E.State==Recursive && E.Str.size() == Str.size() &&
10266  "This is not the same Recursive entry");
10267  // The parent container was not recursive after all, so we could have used
10268  // this Recursive sub-member entry after all, but we assumed the worse when
10269  // we started viz: IncompleteCount!=0.
10270  return;
10271  }
10272  assert(E.Str.empty() && "Entry already present");
10273  E.Str = Str.str();
10274  E.State = IsRecursive? Recursive : NonRecursive;
10275 }
10276 
10277 /// Return a cached TypeString encoding for the ID. If there isn't one, or we
10278 /// are recursively expanding a type (IncompleteCount != 0) and the cached
10279 /// encoding is Recursive, return an empty StringRef.
10280 StringRef TypeStringCache::lookupStr(const IdentifierInfo *ID) {
10281  if (!ID)
10282  return StringRef(); // We have no key.
10283  auto I = Map.find(ID);
10284  if (I == Map.end())
10285  return StringRef(); // We have no encoding.
10286  Entry &E = I->second;
10287  if (E.State == Recursive && IncompleteCount)
10288  return StringRef(); // We don't use Recursive encodings for member types.
10289 
10290  if (E.State == Incomplete) {
10291  // The incomplete type is being used to break out of recursion.
10292  E.State = IncompleteUsed;
10293  ++IncompleteUsedCount;
10294  }
10295  return E.Str;
10296 }
10297 
10298 /// The XCore ABI includes a type information section that communicates symbol
10299 /// type information to the linker. The linker uses this information to verify
10300 /// safety/correctness of things such as array bound and pointers et al.
10301 /// The ABI only requires C (and XC) language modules to emit TypeStrings.
10302 /// This type information (TypeString) is emitted into meta data for all global
10303 /// symbols: definitions, declarations, functions & variables.
10304 ///
10305 /// The TypeString carries type, qualifier, name, size & value details.
10306 /// Please see 'Tools Development Guide' section 2.16.2 for format details:
10307 /// https://www.xmos.com/download/public/Tools-Development-Guide%28X9114A%29.pdf
10308 /// The output is tested by test/CodeGen/xcore-stringtype.c.
10309 ///
10310 static bool getTypeString(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const Decl *D,
10311  const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
10312  TypeStringCache &TSC);
10313 
10314 /// XCore uses emitTargetMD to emit TypeString metadata for global symbols.
10315 void XCoreTargetCodeGenInfo::emitTargetMD(
10316  const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
10317  const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const {
10318  SmallStringEnc Enc;
10319  if (getTypeString(Enc, D, CGM, TSC)) {
10320  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = CGM.getModule().getContext();
10321  llvm::Metadata *MDVals[] = {llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(GV),
10322  llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, Enc.str())};
10323  llvm::NamedMDNode *MD =
10324  CGM.getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata("xcore.typestrings");
10325  MD->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, MDVals));
10326  }
10327 }
10328 
10329 void XCoreTargetCodeGenInfo::emitTargetMetadata(
10330  CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
10331  const llvm::MapVector<GlobalDecl, StringRef> &MangledDeclNames) const {
10332  // Warning, new MangledDeclNames may be appended within this loop.
10333  // We rely on MapVector insertions adding new elements to the end
10334  // of the container.
10335  for (unsigned I = 0; I != MangledDeclNames.size(); ++I) {
10336  auto Val = *(MangledDeclNames.begin() + I);
10337  llvm::GlobalValue *GV = CGM.GetGlobalValue(Val.second);
10338  if (GV) {
10339  const Decl *D = Val.first.getDecl()->getMostRecentDecl();
10340  emitTargetMD(D, GV, CGM);
10341  }
10342  }
10343 }

10347 // SPIR-V.

10350 namespace {
10351 class CommonSPIRABIInfo : public DefaultABIInfo {
10352 public:
10353  CommonSPIRABIInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT) : DefaultABIInfo(CGT) { setCCs(); }
10354 
10355  ABIArgInfo classifyKernelArgumentType(QualType Ty) const;
10356 
10357  // Add new functions rather than overload existing so that these public APIs
10358  // can't be blindly misused with wrong calling convention.
10359  ABIArgInfo classifyRegcallReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
10360  ABIArgInfo classifyRegcallArgumentType(QualType RetTy) const;
10361 
10362  void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
10363 
10364 private:
10365  void setCCs();
10366 };
10367 
10368 ABIArgInfo CommonSPIRABIInfo::classifyKernelArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
10369  Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
10370 
10371  if (getContext().getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice && isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
10372  // Pass all aggregate types allowed by Sema by value.
10373  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty);
10374  }
10375 
10376  return DefaultABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(Ty);
10377 }
10378 
10379 void CommonSPIRABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
10380  llvm::CallingConv::ID CC = FI.getCallingConvention();
10381  bool IsRegCall = CC == llvm::CallingConv::X86_RegCall;
10382 
10383  if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI)) {
10384  CanQualType RetT = FI.getReturnType();
10385  FI.getReturnInfo() =
10386  IsRegCall ? classifyRegcallReturnType(RetT) : classifyReturnType(RetT);
10387  }
10388 
10389  for (auto &Arg : FI.arguments()) {
10390  if (CC == llvm::CallingConv::SPIR_KERNEL) {
10391  Arg.info = classifyKernelArgumentType(Arg.type);
10392  } else {
10393  Arg.info = IsRegCall ? classifyRegcallArgumentType(Arg.type)
10394  : classifyArgumentType(Arg.type);
10395  }
10396  }
10397 }
10398 
10399 // The two functions below are based on AMDGPUABIInfo, but without any
10400 // restriction on the maximum number of arguments passed via registers.
10401 // SPIRV BEs are expected to further adjust the calling convention as
10402 // needed (use stack or byval-like passing) for some of the arguments.
10403 
10404 ABIArgInfo CommonSPIRABIInfo::classifyRegcallReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
10405  if (isAggregateTypeForABI(RetTy)) {
10406  // Records with non-trivial destructors/copy-constructors should not be
10407  // returned by value.
10408  if (!getRecordArgABI(RetTy, getCXXABI())) {
10409  // Ignore empty structs/unions.
10410  if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), RetTy, true))
10411  return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
10412 
10413  // Lower single-element structs to just return a regular value.
10414  if (const Type *SeltTy = isSingleElementStruct(RetTy, getContext()))
10415  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CGT.ConvertType(QualType(SeltTy, 0)));
10416 
10417  if (const RecordType *RT = RetTy->getAs<RecordType>()) {
10418  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
10419  if (RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
10420  return classifyReturnType(RetTy);
10421  }
10422 
10423  // Pack aggregates <= 8 bytes into a single vector register or pair.
10424  // TODO make this parameterizeable/adjustable depending on spir target
10425  // triple abi component.
10426  uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy);
10427  if (Size <= 16)
10428  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(getVMContext()));
10429 
10430  if (Size <= 32)
10431  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()));
10432 
10433  if (Size <= 64) {
10434  llvm::Type *I32Ty = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext());
10435  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::ArrayType::get(I32Ty, 2));
10436  }
10437  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
10438  }
10439  }
10440  // Otherwise just do the default thing.
10441  return classifyReturnType(RetTy);
10442 }
10443 
10444 ABIArgInfo CommonSPIRABIInfo::classifyRegcallArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
10445  Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
10446 
10447  if (isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty)) {
10448  // Records with non-trivial destructors/copy-constructors should not be
10449  // passed by value.
10450  if (auto RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI()))
10451  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, RAA == CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
10452 
10453  // Ignore empty structs/unions.
10454  if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
10455  return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
10456 
10457  // Lower single-element structs to just pass a regular value. TODO: We
10458  // could do reasonable-size multiple-element structs too, using getExpand(),
10459  // though watch out for things like bitfields.
10460  if (const Type *SeltTy = isSingleElementStruct(Ty, getContext()))
10461  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(CGT.ConvertType(QualType(SeltTy, 0)));
10462 
10463  if (const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>()) {
10464  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
10465  if (RD->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
10466  return classifyArgumentType(Ty);
10467  }
10468 
10469  // Pack aggregates <= 8 bytes into single vector register or pair.
10470  // TODO make this parameterizeable/adjustable depending on spir target
10471  // triple abi component.
10472  uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
10473  if (Size <= 64) {
10474  if (Size <= 16)
10475  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(getVMContext()));
10476 
10477  if (Size <= 32)
10478  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext()));
10479 
10480  // XXX: Should this be i64 instead, and should the limit increase?
10481  llvm::Type *I32Ty = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(getVMContext());
10482  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::ArrayType::get(I32Ty, 2));
10483  }
10484  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
10485  }
10486 
10487  // Otherwise just do the default thing.
10488  return classifyArgumentType(Ty);
10489 }
10490

10525 void CommonSPIRABIInfo::setCCs() {
10526  assert(getRuntimeCC() == llvm::CallingConv::C);
10527  RuntimeCC = llvm::CallingConv::SPIR_FUNC;
10528 }
10529 
10530 ABIArgInfo SPIRVABIInfo::classifyKernelArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
10531  if (getContext().getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) {
10532  // Coerce pointer arguments with default address space to CrossWorkGroup
10533  // pointers for HIPSPV/CUDASPV. When the language mode is HIP/CUDA, the
10534  // SPIRTargetInfo maps cuda_device to SPIR-V's CrossWorkGroup address space.
10535  llvm::Type *LTy = CGT.ConvertType(Ty);
10536  auto DefaultAS = getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default);
10537  auto GlobalAS = getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::cuda_device);
10538  auto *PtrTy = llvm::dyn_cast<llvm::PointerType>(LTy);
10539  if (PtrTy && PtrTy->getAddressSpace() == DefaultAS) {
10540  LTy = llvm::PointerType::getWithSamePointeeType(PtrTy, GlobalAS);
10541  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(LTy, 0, nullptr, false);
10542  }
10543  }
10544  return classifyArgumentType(Ty);
10545 }
10546 
10547 void SPIRVABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
10548  // The logic is same as in DefaultABIInfo with an exception on the kernel
10549  // arguments handling.
10550  llvm::CallingConv::ID CC = FI.getCallingConvention();
10551 
10552  if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
10553  FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
10554 
10555  for (auto &I : FI.arguments()) {
10556  if (CC == llvm::CallingConv::SPIR_KERNEL) {
10557  I.info = classifyKernelArgumentType(I.type);
10558  } else {
10559  I.info = classifyArgumentType(I.type);
10560  }
10561  }
10562 }

10568  SPIRVABIInfo(CGM.getTypes()).computeInfo(FI);
10569  else
10570  CommonSPIRABIInfo(CGM.getTypes()).computeInfo(FI);
10571 }
10572 }
10573 }
