10592 
10593 static bool appendType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, QualType QType,
10594  const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
10595  TypeStringCache &TSC);
10596 
10597 /// Helper function for appendRecordType().
10598 /// Builds a SmallVector containing the encoded field types in declaration
10599 /// order.
10600 static bool extractFieldType(SmallVectorImpl<FieldEncoding> &FE,
10601  const RecordDecl *RD,
10602  const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
10603  TypeStringCache &TSC) {
10604  for (const auto *Field : RD->fields()) {
10605  SmallStringEnc Enc;
10606  Enc += "m(";
10607  Enc += Field->getName();
10608  Enc += "){";
10609  if (Field->isBitField()) {
10610  Enc += "b(";
10611  llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(Enc);
10612  OS << Field->getBitWidthValue(CGM.getContext());
10613  Enc += ':';
10614  }
10615  if (!appendType(Enc, Field->getType(), CGM, TSC))
10616  return false;
10617  if (Field->isBitField())
10618  Enc += ')';
10619  Enc += '}';
10620  FE.emplace_back(!Field->getName().empty(), Enc);
10621  }
10622  return true;
10623 }
10624 
10625 /// Appends structure and union types to Enc and adds encoding to cache.
10626 /// Recursively calls appendType (via extractFieldType) for each field.
10627 /// Union types have their fields ordered according to the ABI.
10628 static bool appendRecordType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const RecordType *RT,
10629  const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
10630  TypeStringCache &TSC, const IdentifierInfo *ID) {
10631  // Append the cached TypeString if we have one.
10632  StringRef TypeString = TSC.lookupStr(ID);
10633  if (!TypeString.empty()) {
10634  Enc += TypeString;
10635  return true;
10636  }
10637 
10638  // Start to emit an incomplete TypeString.
10639  size_t Start = Enc.size();
10640  Enc += (RT->isUnionType()? 'u' : 's');
10641  Enc += '(';
10642  if (ID)
10643  Enc += ID->getName();
10644  Enc += "){";
10645 
10646  // We collect all encoded fields and order as necessary.
10647  bool IsRecursive = false;
10648  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl()->getDefinition();
10649  if (RD && !RD->field_empty()) {
10650  // An incomplete TypeString stub is placed in the cache for this RecordType
10651  // so that recursive calls to this RecordType will use it whilst building a
10652  // complete TypeString for this RecordType.
10653  SmallVector<FieldEncoding, 16> FE;
10654  std::string StubEnc(Enc.substr(Start).str());
10655  StubEnc += '}'; // StubEnc now holds a valid incomplete TypeString.
10656  TSC.addIncomplete(ID, std::move(StubEnc));
10657  if (!extractFieldType(FE, RD, CGM, TSC)) {
10658  (void) TSC.removeIncomplete(ID);
10659  return false;
10660  }
10661  IsRecursive = TSC.removeIncomplete(ID);
10662  // The ABI requires unions to be sorted but not structures.
10663  // See FieldEncoding::operator< for sort algorithm.
10664  if (RT->isUnionType())
10665  llvm::sort(FE);
10666  // We can now complete the TypeString.
10667  unsigned E = FE.size();
10668  for (unsigned I = 0; I != E; ++I) {
10669  if (I)
10670  Enc += ',';
10671  Enc += FE[I].str();
10672  }
10673  }
10674  Enc += '}';
10675  TSC.addIfComplete(ID, Enc.substr(Start), IsRecursive);
10676  return true;
10677 }
10678 
10679 /// Appends enum types to Enc and adds the encoding to the cache.
10680 static bool appendEnumType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const EnumType *ET,
10681  TypeStringCache &TSC,
10682  const IdentifierInfo *ID) {
10683  // Append the cached TypeString if we have one.
10684  StringRef TypeString = TSC.lookupStr(ID);
10685  if (!TypeString.empty()) {
10686  Enc += TypeString;
10687  return true;
10688  }
10689 
10690  size_t Start = Enc.size();
10691  Enc += "e(";
10692  if (ID)
10693  Enc += ID->getName();
10694  Enc += "){";
10695 
10696  // We collect all encoded enumerations and order them alphanumerically.
10697  if (const EnumDecl *ED = ET->getDecl()->getDefinition()) {
10698  SmallVector<FieldEncoding, 16> FE;
10699  for (auto I = ED->enumerator_begin(), E = ED->enumerator_end(); I != E;
10700  ++I) {
10701  SmallStringEnc EnumEnc;
10702  EnumEnc += "m(";
10703  EnumEnc += I->getName();
10704  EnumEnc += "){";
10705  I->getInitVal().toString(EnumEnc);
10706  EnumEnc += '}';
10707  FE.push_back(FieldEncoding(!I->getName().empty(), EnumEnc));
10708  }
10709  llvm::sort(FE);
10710  unsigned E = FE.size();
10711  for (unsigned I = 0; I != E; ++I) {
10712  if (I)
10713  Enc += ',';
10714  Enc += FE[I].str();
10715  }
10716  }
10717  Enc += '}';
10718  TSC.addIfComplete(ID, Enc.substr(Start), false);
10719  return true;
10720 }
10721 
10722 /// Appends type's qualifier to Enc.
10723 /// This is done prior to appending the type's encoding.
10724 static void appendQualifier(SmallStringEnc &Enc, QualType QT) {
10725  // Qualifiers are emitted in alphabetical order.
10726  static const char *const Table[]={"","c:","r:","cr:","v:","cv:","rv:","crv:"};
10727  int Lookup = 0;
10728  if (QT.isConstQualified())
10729  Lookup += 1<<0;
10730  if (QT.isRestrictQualified())
10731  Lookup += 1<<1;
10732  if (QT.isVolatileQualified())
10733  Lookup += 1<<2;
10734  Enc += Table[Lookup];
10735 }
10736 
10737 /// Appends built-in types to Enc.
10738 static bool appendBuiltinType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const BuiltinType *BT) {
10739  const char *EncType;
10740  switch (BT->getKind()) {
10741  case BuiltinType::Void:
10742  EncType = "0";
10743  break;
10744  case BuiltinType::Bool:
10745  EncType = "b";
10746  break;
10747  case BuiltinType::Char_U:
10748  EncType = "uc";
10749  break;
10750  case BuiltinType::UChar:
10751  EncType = "uc";
10752  break;
10753  case BuiltinType::SChar:
10754  EncType = "sc";
10755  break;
10756  case BuiltinType::UShort:
10757  EncType = "us";
10758  break;
10759  case BuiltinType::Short:
10760  EncType = "ss";
10761  break;
10762  case BuiltinType::UInt:
10763  EncType = "ui";
10764  break;
10765  case BuiltinType::Int:
10766  EncType = "si";
10767  break;
10768  case BuiltinType::ULong:
10769  EncType = "ul";
10770  break;
10771  case BuiltinType::Long:
10772  EncType = "sl";
10773  break;
10774  case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
10775  EncType = "ull";
10776  break;
10777  case BuiltinType::LongLong:
10778  EncType = "sll";
10779  break;
10780  case BuiltinType::Float:
10781  EncType = "ft";
10782  break;
10783  case BuiltinType::Double:
10784  EncType = "d";
10785  break;
10786  case BuiltinType::LongDouble:
10787  EncType = "ld";
10788  break;
10789  default:
10790  return false;
10791  }
10792  Enc += EncType;
10793  return true;
10794 }
10795 
10796 /// Appends a pointer encoding to Enc before calling appendType for the pointee.
10797 static bool appendPointerType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const PointerType *PT,
10798  const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
10799  TypeStringCache &TSC) {
10800  Enc += "p(";
10801  if (!appendType(Enc, PT->getPointeeType(), CGM, TSC))
10802  return false;
10803  Enc += ')';
10804  return true;
10805 }
10806 
10807 /// Appends array encoding to Enc before calling appendType for the element.
10808 static bool appendArrayType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, QualType QT,
10809  const ArrayType *AT,
10810  const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
10811  TypeStringCache &TSC, StringRef NoSizeEnc) {
10812  if (AT->getSizeModifier() != ArrayType::Normal)
10813  return false;
10814  Enc += "a(";
10815  if (const ConstantArrayType *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
10816  CAT->getSize().toStringUnsigned(Enc);
10817  else
10818  Enc += NoSizeEnc; // Global arrays use "*", otherwise it is "".
10819  Enc += ':';
10820  // The Qualifiers should be attached to the type rather than the array.
10821  appendQualifier(Enc, QT);
10822  if (!appendType(Enc, AT->getElementType(), CGM, TSC))
10823  return false;
10824  Enc += ')';
10825  return true;
10826 }
10827 
10828 /// Appends a function encoding to Enc, calling appendType for the return type
10829 /// and the arguments.
10830 static bool appendFunctionType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const FunctionType *FT,
10831  const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
10832  TypeStringCache &TSC) {
10833  Enc += "f{";
10834  if (!appendType(Enc, FT->getReturnType(), CGM, TSC))
10835  return false;
10836  Enc += "}(";
10837  if (const FunctionProtoType *FPT = FT->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
10838  // N.B. we are only interested in the adjusted param types.
10839  auto I = FPT->param_type_begin();
10840  auto E = FPT->param_type_end();
10841  if (I != E) {
10842  do {
10843  if (!appendType(Enc, *I, CGM, TSC))
10844  return false;
10845  ++I;
10846  if (I != E)
10847  Enc += ',';
10848  } while (I != E);
10849  if (FPT->isVariadic())
10850  Enc += ",va";
10851  } else {
10852  if (FPT->isVariadic())
10853  Enc += "va";
10854  else
10855  Enc += '0';
10856  }
10857  }
10858  Enc += ')';
10859  return true;
10860 }
10861 
10862 /// Handles the type's qualifier before dispatching a call to handle specific
10863 /// type encodings.
10864 static bool appendType(SmallStringEnc &Enc, QualType QType,
10865  const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
10866  TypeStringCache &TSC) {
10867 
10868  QualType QT = QType.getCanonicalType();
10869 
10870  if (const ArrayType *AT = QT->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe())
10871  // The Qualifiers should be attached to the type rather than the array.
10872  // Thus we don't call appendQualifier() here.
10873  return appendArrayType(Enc, QT, AT, CGM, TSC, "");
10874 
10875  appendQualifier(Enc, QT);
10876 
10877  if (const BuiltinType *BT = QT->getAs<BuiltinType>())
10878  return appendBuiltinType(Enc, BT);
10879 
10880  if (const PointerType *PT = QT->getAs<PointerType>())
10881  return appendPointerType(Enc, PT, CGM, TSC);
10882 
10883  if (const EnumType *ET = QT->getAs<EnumType>())
10884  return appendEnumType(Enc, ET, TSC, QT.getBaseTypeIdentifier());
10885 
10886  if (const RecordType *RT = QT->getAsStructureType())
10887  return appendRecordType(Enc, RT, CGM, TSC, QT.getBaseTypeIdentifier());
10888 
10889  if (const RecordType *RT = QT->getAsUnionType())
10890  return appendRecordType(Enc, RT, CGM, TSC, QT.getBaseTypeIdentifier());
10891 
10892  if (const FunctionType *FT = QT->getAs<FunctionType>())
10893  return appendFunctionType(Enc, FT, CGM, TSC);
10894 
10895  return false;
10896 }
10897 
10898 static bool getTypeString(SmallStringEnc &Enc, const Decl *D,
10899  const CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM,
10900  TypeStringCache &TSC) {
10901  if (!D)
10902  return false;
10903 
10904  if (const FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
10905  if (FD->getLanguageLinkage() != CLanguageLinkage)
10906  return false;
10907  return appendType(Enc, FD->getType(), CGM, TSC);
10908  }
10909 
10910  if (const VarDecl *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
10911  if (VD->getLanguageLinkage() != CLanguageLinkage)
10912  return false;
10913  QualType QT = VD->getType().getCanonicalType();
10914  if (const ArrayType *AT = QT->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe()) {
10915  // Global ArrayTypes are given a size of '*' if the size is unknown.
10916  // The Qualifiers should be attached to the type rather than the array.
10917  // Thus we don't call appendQualifier() here.
10918  return appendArrayType(Enc, QT, AT, CGM, TSC, "*");
10919  }
10920  return appendType(Enc, QT, CGM, TSC);
10921  }
10922  return false;
10923 }
10924 
10925 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
10926 // RISCV ABI Implementation
10927 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
10928 
10929 namespace {
10930 class RISCVABIInfo : public DefaultABIInfo {
10931 private:
10932  // Size of the integer ('x') registers in bits.
10933  unsigned XLen;
10934  // Size of the floating point ('f') registers in bits. Note that the target
10935  // ISA might have a wider FLen than the selected ABI (e.g. an RV32IF target
10936  // with soft float ABI has FLen==0).
10937  unsigned FLen;
10938  static const int NumArgGPRs = 8;
10939  static const int NumArgFPRs = 8;
10940  bool detectFPCCEligibleStructHelper(QualType Ty, CharUnits CurOff,
10941  llvm::Type *&Field1Ty,
10942  CharUnits &Field1Off,
10943  llvm::Type *&Field2Ty,
10944  CharUnits &Field2Off) const;
10945 
10946 public:
10947  RISCVABIInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT, unsigned XLen, unsigned FLen)
10948  : DefaultABIInfo(CGT), XLen(XLen), FLen(FLen) {}
10949 
10950  // DefaultABIInfo's classifyReturnType and classifyArgumentType are
10951  // non-virtual, but computeInfo is virtual, so we overload it.
10952  void computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const override;
10953 
10954  ABIArgInfo classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty, bool IsFixed, int &ArgGPRsLeft,
10955  int &ArgFPRsLeft) const;
10956  ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;
10957 
10958  Address EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
10959  QualType Ty) const override;
10960 
10961  ABIArgInfo extendType(QualType Ty) const;
10962 
10963  bool detectFPCCEligibleStruct(QualType Ty, llvm::Type *&Field1Ty,
10964  CharUnits &Field1Off, llvm::Type *&Field2Ty,
10965  CharUnits &Field2Off, int &NeededArgGPRs,
10966  int &NeededArgFPRs) const;
10967  ABIArgInfo coerceAndExpandFPCCEligibleStruct(llvm::Type *Field1Ty,
10968  CharUnits Field1Off,
10969  llvm::Type *Field2Ty,
10970  CharUnits Field2Off) const;
10971 };
10972 } // end anonymous namespace
10973 
10974 void RISCVABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
10975  QualType RetTy = FI.getReturnType();
10976  if (!getCXXABI().classifyReturnType(FI))
10977  FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(RetTy);
10978 
10979  // IsRetIndirect is true if classifyArgumentType indicated the value should
10980  // be passed indirect, or if the type size is a scalar greater than 2*XLen
10981  // and not a complex type with elements <= FLen. e.g. fp128 is passed direct
10982  // in LLVM IR, relying on the backend lowering code to rewrite the argument
10983  // list and pass indirectly on RV32.
10984  bool IsRetIndirect = FI.getReturnInfo().getKind() == ABIArgInfo::Indirect;
10985  if (!IsRetIndirect && RetTy->isScalarType() &&
10986  getContext().getTypeSize(RetTy) > (2 * XLen)) {
10987  if (RetTy->isComplexType() && FLen) {
10988  QualType EltTy = RetTy->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
10989  IsRetIndirect = getContext().getTypeSize(EltTy) > FLen;
10990  } else {
10991  // This is a normal scalar > 2*XLen, such as fp128 on RV32.
10992  IsRetIndirect = true;
10993  }
10994  }
10995 
10996  // We must track the number of GPRs used in order to conform to the RISC-V
10997  // ABI, as integer scalars passed in registers should have signext/zeroext
10998  // when promoted, but are anyext if passed on the stack. As GPR usage is
10999  // different for variadic arguments, we must also track whether we are
11000  // examining a vararg or not.
11001  int ArgGPRsLeft = IsRetIndirect ? NumArgGPRs - 1 : NumArgGPRs;
11002  int ArgFPRsLeft = FLen ? NumArgFPRs : 0;
11003  int NumFixedArgs = FI.getNumRequiredArgs();
11004 
11005  int ArgNum = 0;
11006  for (auto &ArgInfo : FI.arguments()) {
11007  bool IsFixed = ArgNum < NumFixedArgs;
11008  ArgInfo.info =
11009  classifyArgumentType(ArgInfo.type, IsFixed, ArgGPRsLeft, ArgFPRsLeft);
11010  ArgNum++;
11011  }
11012 }
11013 
11014 // Returns true if the struct is a potential candidate for the floating point
11015 // calling convention. If this function returns true, the caller is
11016 // responsible for checking that if there is only a single field then that
11017 // field is a float.
11018 bool RISCVABIInfo::detectFPCCEligibleStructHelper(QualType Ty, CharUnits CurOff,
11019  llvm::Type *&Field1Ty,
11020  CharUnits &Field1Off,
11021  llvm::Type *&Field2Ty,
11022  CharUnits &Field2Off) const {
11023  bool IsInt = Ty->isIntegralOrEnumerationType();
11024  bool IsFloat = Ty->isRealFloatingType();
11025 
11026  if (IsInt || IsFloat) {
11027  uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
11028  if (IsInt && Size > XLen)
11029  return false;
11030  // Can't be eligible if larger than the FP registers. Half precision isn't
11031  // currently supported on RISC-V and the ABI hasn't been confirmed, so
11032  // default to the integer ABI in that case.
11033  if (IsFloat && (Size > FLen || Size < 32))
11034  return false;
11035  // Can't be eligible if an integer type was already found (int+int pairs
11036  // are not eligible).
11037  if (IsInt && Field1Ty && Field1Ty->isIntegerTy())
11038  return false;
11039  if (!Field1Ty) {
11040  Field1Ty = CGT.ConvertType(Ty);
11041  Field1Off = CurOff;
11042  return true;
11043  }
11044  if (!Field2Ty) {
11045  Field2Ty = CGT.ConvertType(Ty);
11046  Field2Off = CurOff;
11047  return true;
11048  }
11049  return false;
11050  }
11051 
11052  if (auto CTy = Ty->getAs<ComplexType>()) {
11053  if (Field1Ty)
11054  return false;
11055  QualType EltTy = CTy->getElementType();
11056  if (getContext().getTypeSize(EltTy) > FLen)
11057  return false;
11058  Field1Ty = CGT.ConvertType(EltTy);
11059  Field1Off = CurOff;
11060  Field2Ty = Field1Ty;
11061  Field2Off = Field1Off + getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(EltTy);
11062  return true;
11063  }
11064 
11065  if (const ConstantArrayType *ATy = getContext().getAsConstantArrayType(Ty)) {
11066  uint64_t ArraySize = ATy->getSize().getZExtValue();
11067  QualType EltTy = ATy->getElementType();
11068  CharUnits EltSize = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(EltTy);
11069  for (uint64_t i = 0; i < ArraySize; ++i) {
11070  bool Ret = detectFPCCEligibleStructHelper(EltTy, CurOff, Field1Ty,
11071  Field1Off, Field2Ty, Field2Off);
11072  if (!Ret)
11073  return false;
11074  CurOff += EltSize;
11075  }
11076  return true;
11077  }
11078 
11079  if (const auto *RTy = Ty->getAs<RecordType>()) {
11080  // Structures with either a non-trivial destructor or a non-trivial
11081  // copy constructor are not eligible for the FP calling convention.
11082  if (getRecordArgABI(Ty, CGT.getCXXABI()))
11083  return false;
11084  if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
11085  return true;
11086  const RecordDecl *RD = RTy->getDecl();
11087  // Unions aren't eligible unless they're empty (which is caught above).
11088  if (RD->isUnion())
11089  return false;
11090  int ZeroWidthBitFieldCount = 0;
11091  for (const FieldDecl *FD : RD->fields()) {
11092  const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getContext().getASTRecordLayout(RD);
11093  uint64_t FieldOffInBits = Layout.getFieldOffset(FD->getFieldIndex());
11094  QualType QTy = FD->getType();
11095  if (FD->isBitField()) {
11096  unsigned BitWidth = FD->getBitWidthValue(getContext());
11097  // Allow a bitfield with a type greater than XLen as long as the
11098  // bitwidth is XLen or less.
11099  if (getContext().getTypeSize(QTy) > XLen && BitWidth <= XLen)
11100  QTy = getContext().getIntTypeForBitwidth(XLen, false);
11101  if (BitWidth == 0) {
11102  ZeroWidthBitFieldCount++;
11103  continue;
11104  }
11105  }
11106 
11107  bool Ret = detectFPCCEligibleStructHelper(
11108  QTy, CurOff + getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(FieldOffInBits),
11109  Field1Ty, Field1Off, Field2Ty, Field2Off);
11110  if (!Ret)
11111  return false;
11112 
11113  // As a quirk of the ABI, zero-width bitfields aren't ignored for fp+fp
11114  // or int+fp structs, but are ignored for a struct with an fp field and
11115  // any number of zero-width bitfields.
11116  if (Field2Ty && ZeroWidthBitFieldCount > 0)
11117  return false;
11118  }
11119  return Field1Ty != nullptr;
11120  }
11121 
11122  return false;
11123 }
11124 
11125 // Determine if a struct is eligible for passing according to the floating
11126 // point calling convention (i.e., when flattened it contains a single fp
11127 // value, fp+fp, or int+fp of appropriate size). If so, NeededArgFPRs and
11128 // NeededArgGPRs are incremented appropriately.
11129 bool RISCVABIInfo::detectFPCCEligibleStruct(QualType Ty, llvm::Type *&Field1Ty,
11130  CharUnits &Field1Off,
11131  llvm::Type *&Field2Ty,
11132  CharUnits &Field2Off,
11133  int &NeededArgGPRs,
11134  int &NeededArgFPRs) const {
11135  Field1Ty = nullptr;
11136  Field2Ty = nullptr;
11137  NeededArgGPRs = 0;
11138  NeededArgFPRs = 0;
11139  bool IsCandidate = detectFPCCEligibleStructHelper(
11140  Ty, CharUnits::Zero(), Field1Ty, Field1Off, Field2Ty, Field2Off);
11141  // Not really a candidate if we have a single int but no float.
11142  if (Field1Ty && !Field2Ty && !Field1Ty->isFloatingPointTy())
11143  return false;
11144  if (!IsCandidate)
11145  return false;
11146  if (Field1Ty && Field1Ty->isFloatingPointTy())
11147  NeededArgFPRs++;
11148  else if (Field1Ty)
11149  NeededArgGPRs++;
11150  if (Field2Ty && Field2Ty->isFloatingPointTy())
11151  NeededArgFPRs++;
11152  else if (Field2Ty)
11153  NeededArgGPRs++;
11154  return true;
11155 }
11156 
11157 // Call getCoerceAndExpand for the two-element flattened struct described by
11158 // Field1Ty, Field1Off, Field2Ty, Field2Off. This method will create an
11159 // appropriate coerceToType and unpaddedCoerceToType.
11160 ABIArgInfo RISCVABIInfo::coerceAndExpandFPCCEligibleStruct(
11161  llvm::Type *Field1Ty, CharUnits Field1Off, llvm::Type *Field2Ty,
11162  CharUnits Field2Off) const {
11163  SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 3> CoerceElts;
11164  SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 2> UnpaddedCoerceElts;
11165  if (!Field1Off.isZero())
11166  CoerceElts.push_back(llvm::ArrayType::get(
11167  llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(getVMContext()), Field1Off.getQuantity()));
11168 
11169  CoerceElts.push_back(Field1Ty);
11170  UnpaddedCoerceElts.push_back(Field1Ty);
11171 
11172  if (!Field2Ty) {
11173  return ABIArgInfo::getCoerceAndExpand(
11174  llvm::StructType::get(getVMContext(), CoerceElts, !Field1Off.isZero()),
11175  UnpaddedCoerceElts[0]);
11176  }
11177 
11178  CharUnits Field2Align =
11179  CharUnits::fromQuantity(getDataLayout().getABITypeAlignment(Field2Ty));
11180  CharUnits Field1End = Field1Off +
11181  CharUnits::fromQuantity(getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSize(Field1Ty));
11182  CharUnits Field2OffNoPadNoPack = Field1End.alignTo(Field2Align);
11183 
11184  CharUnits Padding = CharUnits::Zero();
11185  if (Field2Off > Field2OffNoPadNoPack)
11186  Padding = Field2Off - Field2OffNoPadNoPack;
11187  else if (Field2Off != Field2Align && Field2Off > Field1End)
11188  Padding = Field2Off - Field1End;
11189 
11190  bool IsPacked = !Field2Off.isMultipleOf(Field2Align);
11191 
11192  if (!Padding.isZero())
11193  CoerceElts.push_back(llvm::ArrayType::get(
11194  llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(getVMContext()), Padding.getQuantity()));
11195 
11196  CoerceElts.push_back(Field2Ty);
11197  UnpaddedCoerceElts.push_back(Field2Ty);
11198 
11199  auto CoerceToType =
11200  llvm::StructType::get(getVMContext(), CoerceElts, IsPacked);
11201  auto UnpaddedCoerceToType =
11202  llvm::StructType::get(getVMContext(), UnpaddedCoerceElts, IsPacked);
11203 
11204  return ABIArgInfo::getCoerceAndExpand(CoerceToType, UnpaddedCoerceToType);
11205 }
11206 
11207 ABIArgInfo RISCVABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty, bool IsFixed,
11208  int &ArgGPRsLeft,
11209  int &ArgFPRsLeft) const {
11210  assert(ArgGPRsLeft <= NumArgGPRs && "Arg GPR tracking underflow");
11211  Ty = useFirstFieldIfTransparentUnion(Ty);
11212 
11213  // Structures with either a non-trivial destructor or a non-trivial
11214  // copy constructor are always passed indirectly.
11215  if (CGCXXABI::RecordArgABI RAA = getRecordArgABI(Ty, getCXXABI())) {
11216  if (ArgGPRsLeft)
11217  ArgGPRsLeft -= 1;
11218  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/RAA ==
11219  CGCXXABI::RAA_DirectInMemory);
11220  }
11221 
11222  // Ignore empty structs/unions.
11223  if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true))
11224  return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
11225 
11226  uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
11227 
11228  // Pass floating point values via FPRs if possible.
11229  if (IsFixed && Ty->isFloatingType() && !Ty->isComplexType() &&
11230  FLen >= Size && ArgFPRsLeft) {
11231  ArgFPRsLeft--;
11232  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
11233  }
11234 
11235  // Complex types for the hard float ABI must be passed direct rather than
11236  // using CoerceAndExpand.
11237  if (IsFixed && Ty->isComplexType() && FLen && ArgFPRsLeft >= 2) {
11238  QualType EltTy = Ty->castAs<ComplexType>()->getElementType();
11239  if (getContext().getTypeSize(EltTy) <= FLen) {
11240  ArgFPRsLeft -= 2;
11241  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
11242  }
11243  }
11244 
11245  if (IsFixed && FLen && Ty->isStructureOrClassType()) {
11246  llvm::Type *Field1Ty = nullptr;
11247  llvm::Type *Field2Ty = nullptr;
11248  CharUnits Field1Off = CharUnits::Zero();
11249  CharUnits Field2Off = CharUnits::Zero();
11250  int NeededArgGPRs = 0;
11251  int NeededArgFPRs = 0;
11252  bool IsCandidate =
11253  detectFPCCEligibleStruct(Ty, Field1Ty, Field1Off, Field2Ty, Field2Off,
11254  NeededArgGPRs, NeededArgFPRs);
11255  if (IsCandidate && NeededArgGPRs <= ArgGPRsLeft &&
11256  NeededArgFPRs <= ArgFPRsLeft) {
11257  ArgGPRsLeft -= NeededArgGPRs;
11258  ArgFPRsLeft -= NeededArgFPRs;
11259  return coerceAndExpandFPCCEligibleStruct(Field1Ty, Field1Off, Field2Ty,
11260  Field2Off);
11261  }
11262  }
11263 
11264  uint64_t NeededAlign = getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty);
11265  bool MustUseStack = false;
11266  // Determine the number of GPRs needed to pass the current argument
11267  // according to the ABI. 2*XLen-aligned varargs are passed in "aligned"
11268  // register pairs, so may consume 3 registers.
11269  int NeededArgGPRs = 1;
11270  if (!IsFixed && NeededAlign == 2 * XLen)
11271  NeededArgGPRs = 2 + (ArgGPRsLeft % 2);
11272  else if (Size > XLen && Size <= 2 * XLen)
11273  NeededArgGPRs = 2;
11274 
11275  if (NeededArgGPRs > ArgGPRsLeft) {
11276  MustUseStack = true;
11277  NeededArgGPRs = ArgGPRsLeft;
11278  }
11279 
11280  ArgGPRsLeft -= NeededArgGPRs;
11281 
11282  if (!isAggregateTypeForABI(Ty) && !Ty->isVectorType()) {
11283  // Treat an enum type as its underlying type.
11284  if (const EnumType *EnumTy = Ty->getAs<EnumType>())
11285  Ty = EnumTy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
11286 
11287  // All integral types are promoted to XLen width, unless passed on the
11288  // stack.
11289  if (Size < XLen && Ty->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() && !MustUseStack) {
11290  return extendType(Ty);
11291  }
11292 
11293  if (const auto *EIT = Ty->getAs<BitIntType>()) {
11294  if (EIT->getNumBits() < XLen && !MustUseStack)
11295  return extendType(Ty);
11296  if (EIT->getNumBits() > 128 ||
11297  (!getContext().getTargetInfo().hasInt128Type() &&
11298  EIT->getNumBits() > 64))
11299  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false);
11300  }
11301 
11302  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
11303  }
11304 
11305  // Aggregates which are <= 2*XLen will be passed in registers if possible,
11306  // so coerce to integers.
11307  if (Size <= 2 * XLen) {
11308  unsigned Alignment = getContext().getTypeAlign(Ty);
11309 
11310  // Use a single XLen int if possible, 2*XLen if 2*XLen alignment is
11311  // required, and a 2-element XLen array if only XLen alignment is required.
11312  if (Size <= XLen) {
11313  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(
11314  llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), XLen));
11315  } else if (Alignment == 2 * XLen) {
11316  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(
11317  llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), 2 * XLen));
11318  } else {
11319  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect(llvm::ArrayType::get(
11320  llvm::IntegerType::get(getVMContext(), XLen), 2));
11321  }
11322  }
11323  return getNaturalAlignIndirect(Ty, /*ByVal=*/false);
11324 }
11325 
11326 ABIArgInfo RISCVABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const {
11327  if (RetTy->isVoidType())
11328  return ABIArgInfo::getIgnore();
11329 
11330  int ArgGPRsLeft = 2;
11331  int ArgFPRsLeft = FLen ? 2 : 0;
11332 
11333  // The rules for return and argument types are the same, so defer to
11334  // classifyArgumentType.
11335  return classifyArgumentType(RetTy, /*IsFixed=*/true, ArgGPRsLeft,
11336  ArgFPRsLeft);
11337 }
11338 
11339 Address RISCVABIInfo::EmitVAArg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Address VAListAddr,
11340  QualType Ty) const {
11341  CharUnits SlotSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(XLen / 8);
11342 
11343  // Empty records are ignored for parameter passing purposes.
11344  if (isEmptyRecord(getContext(), Ty, true)) {
11345  Address Addr = Address(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(VAListAddr),
11346  getVAListElementType(CGF), SlotSize);
11347  Addr = CGF.Builder.CreateElementBitCast(Addr, CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(Ty));
11348  return Addr;
11349  }
11350 
11351  auto TInfo = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(Ty);
11352 
11353  // Arguments bigger than 2*Xlen bytes are passed indirectly.
11354  bool IsIndirect = TInfo.Width > 2 * SlotSize;
11355 
11356  return emitVoidPtrVAArg(CGF, VAListAddr, Ty, IsIndirect, TInfo,
11357  SlotSize, /*AllowHigherAlign=*/true);
11358 }
11359 
11360 ABIArgInfo RISCVABIInfo::extendType(QualType Ty) const {
11361  int TySize = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
11362  // RV64 ABI requires unsigned 32 bit integers to be sign extended.
11363  if (XLen == 64 && Ty->isUnsignedIntegerOrEnumerationType() && TySize == 32)
11364  return ABIArgInfo::getSignExtend(Ty);
11365  return ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty);
11366 }
11367 
11368 namespace {
11369 class RISCVTargetCodeGenInfo : public TargetCodeGenInfo {
11370 public:
11371  RISCVTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGen::CodeGenTypes &CGT, unsigned XLen,
11372  unsigned FLen)
11373  : TargetCodeGenInfo(std::make_unique<RISCVABIInfo>(CGT, XLen, FLen)) {}
11374 
11375  void setTargetAttributes(const Decl *D, llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
11376  CodeGen::CodeGenModule &CGM) const override {
11377  const auto *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D);
11378  if (!FD) return;
11379 
11380  const auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<RISCVInterruptAttr>();
11381  if (!Attr)
11382  return;
11383 
11384  const char *Kind;
11385  switch (Attr->getInterrupt()) {
11386  case RISCVInterruptAttr::user: Kind = "user"; break;
11387  case RISCVInterruptAttr::supervisor: Kind = "supervisor"; break;
11388  case RISCVInterruptAttr::machine: Kind = "machine"; break;
11389  }
11390 
11391  auto *Fn = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
11392 
11393  Fn->addFnAttr("interrupt", Kind);
11394  }
11395 };
11396 } // namespace

11401 namespace {
11402 class VEABIInfo : public DefaultABIInfo {
11403 public:
11404  VEABIInfo(CodeGenTypes &CGT) : DefaultABIInfo(CGT) {}
11405 
11406 private:
11407  ABIArgInfo classifyReturnType(QualType RetTy) const;

11412 
11413 ABIArgInfo VEABIInfo::classifyReturnType(QualType Ty) const {
11414  if (Ty->isAnyComplexType())
11415  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
11416  uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
11417  if (Size < 64 && Ty->isIntegerType())
11418  return ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty);
11419  return DefaultABIInfo::classifyReturnType(Ty);
11420 }
11421 
11422 ABIArgInfo VEABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(QualType Ty) const {
11423  if (Ty->isAnyComplexType())
11424  return ABIArgInfo::getDirect();
11425  uint64_t Size = getContext().getTypeSize(Ty);
11426  if (Size < 64 && Ty->isIntegerType())
11427  return ABIArgInfo::getExtend(Ty);
11428  return DefaultABIInfo::classifyArgumentType(Ty);
11429 }
11430 
11431 void VEABIInfo::computeInfo(CGFunctionInfo &FI) const {
11432  FI.getReturnInfo() = classifyReturnType(FI.getReturnType());
11433  for (auto &Arg : FI.arguments())
11434  Arg.info = classifyArgumentType(Arg.type);
11435 }

11458 
11459 const TargetCodeGenInfo &CodeGenModule::getTargetCodeGenInfo() {
11460  if (TheTargetCodeGenInfo)
11461  return *TheTargetCodeGenInfo;
11462 
11463  // Helper to set the unique_ptr while still keeping the return value.
11464  auto SetCGInfo = [&](TargetCodeGenInfo *P) -> const TargetCodeGenInfo & {
11465  this->TheTargetCodeGenInfo.reset(P);
11466  return *P;
11467  };
11468 
11469  const llvm::Triple &Triple = getTarget().getTriple();
11470  switch (Triple.getArch()) {
11471  default:
11472  return SetCGInfo(new DefaultTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11473 
11474  case llvm::Triple::le32:
11475  return SetCGInfo(new PNaClTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11476  case llvm::Triple::m68k:
11477  return SetCGInfo(new M68kTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11478  case llvm::Triple::mips:
11479  case llvm::Triple::mipsel:
11480  if (Triple.getOS() == llvm::Triple::NaCl)
11481  return SetCGInfo(new PNaClTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11482  return SetCGInfo(new MIPSTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, true));
11483 
11484  case llvm::Triple::mips64:
11485  case llvm::Triple::mips64el:
11486  return SetCGInfo(new MIPSTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, false));
11487 
11488  case llvm::Triple::avr: {
11489  // For passing parameters, R8~R25 are used on avr, and R18~R25 are used
11490  // on avrtiny. For passing return value, R18~R25 are used on avr, and
11491  // R22~R25 are used on avrtiny.
11492  unsigned NPR = getTarget().getABI() == "avrtiny" ? 6 : 18;
11493  unsigned NRR = getTarget().getABI() == "avrtiny" ? 4 : 8;
11494  return SetCGInfo(new AVRTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, NPR, NRR));
11495  }
11496 
11497  case llvm::Triple::aarch64:
11498  case llvm::Triple::aarch64_32:
11499  case llvm::Triple::aarch64_be: {
11500  AArch64ABIInfo::ABIKind Kind = AArch64ABIInfo::AAPCS;
11501  if (getTarget().getABI() == "darwinpcs")
11502  Kind = AArch64ABIInfo::DarwinPCS;
11503  else if (Triple.isOSWindows())
11504  return SetCGInfo(
11505  new WindowsAArch64TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, AArch64ABIInfo::Win64));
11506 
11507  return SetCGInfo(new AArch64TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, Kind));
11508  }
11509 
11510  case llvm::Triple::wasm32:
11511  case llvm::Triple::wasm64: {
11512  WebAssemblyABIInfo::ABIKind Kind = WebAssemblyABIInfo::MVP;
11513  if (getTarget().getABI() == "experimental-mv")
11514  Kind = WebAssemblyABIInfo::ExperimentalMV;
11515  return SetCGInfo(new WebAssemblyTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, Kind));
11516  }
11517 
11518  case llvm::Triple::arm:
11519  case llvm::Triple::armeb:
11520  case llvm::Triple::thumb:
11521  case llvm::Triple::thumbeb: {
11522  if (Triple.getOS() == llvm::Triple::Win32) {
11523  return SetCGInfo(
11524  new WindowsARMTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, ARMABIInfo::AAPCS_VFP));
11525  }
11526 
11527  ARMABIInfo::ABIKind Kind = ARMABIInfo::AAPCS;
11528  StringRef ABIStr = getTarget().getABI();
11529  if (ABIStr == "apcs-gnu")
11530  Kind = ARMABIInfo::APCS;
11531  else if (ABIStr == "aapcs16")
11532  Kind = ARMABIInfo::AAPCS16_VFP;
11533  else if (CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "hard" ||
11534  (CodeGenOpts.FloatABI != "soft" &&
11535  (Triple.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUEABIHF ||
11536  Triple.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::MuslEABIHF ||
11537  Triple.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::EABIHF)))
11538  Kind = ARMABIInfo::AAPCS_VFP;
11539 
11540  return SetCGInfo(new ARMTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, Kind));
11541  }
11542 
11543  case llvm::Triple::ppc: {
11544  if (Triple.isOSAIX())
11545  return SetCGInfo(new AIXTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, /*Is64Bit*/ false));
11546 
11547  bool IsSoftFloat =
11548  CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft" || getTarget().hasFeature("spe");
11549  bool RetSmallStructInRegABI =
11550  PPC32TargetCodeGenInfo::isStructReturnInRegABI(Triple, CodeGenOpts);
11551  return SetCGInfo(
11552  new PPC32TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, IsSoftFloat, RetSmallStructInRegABI));
11553  }
11554  case llvm::Triple::ppcle: {
11555  bool IsSoftFloat = CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft";
11556  bool RetSmallStructInRegABI =
11557  PPC32TargetCodeGenInfo::isStructReturnInRegABI(Triple, CodeGenOpts);
11558  return SetCGInfo(
11559  new PPC32TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, IsSoftFloat, RetSmallStructInRegABI));
11560  }
11561  case llvm::Triple::ppc64:
11562  if (Triple.isOSAIX())
11563  return SetCGInfo(new AIXTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, /*Is64Bit*/ true));
11564 
11565  if (Triple.isOSBinFormatELF()) {
11566  PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::ABIKind Kind = PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::ELFv1;
11567  if (getTarget().getABI() == "elfv2")
11568  Kind = PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::ELFv2;
11569  bool IsSoftFloat = CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft";
11570 
11571  return SetCGInfo(
11572  new PPC64_SVR4_TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, Kind, IsSoftFloat));
11573  }
11574  return SetCGInfo(new PPC64TargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11575  case llvm::Triple::ppc64le: {
11576  assert(Triple.isOSBinFormatELF() && "PPC64 LE non-ELF not supported!");
11577  PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::ABIKind Kind = PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::ELFv2;
11578  if (getTarget().getABI() == "elfv1")
11579  Kind = PPC64_SVR4_ABIInfo::ELFv1;
11580  bool IsSoftFloat = CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft";
11581 
11582  return SetCGInfo(
11583  new PPC64_SVR4_TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, Kind, IsSoftFloat));
11584  }
11585 
11586  case llvm::Triple::nvptx:
11587  case llvm::Triple::nvptx64:
11588  return SetCGInfo(new NVPTXTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11589 
11590  case llvm::Triple::msp430:
11591  return SetCGInfo(new MSP430TargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11592 
11593  case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
11594  case llvm::Triple::riscv64: {
11595  StringRef ABIStr = getTarget().getABI();
11596  unsigned XLen = getTarget().getPointerWidth(0);
11597  unsigned ABIFLen = 0;
11598  if (ABIStr.endswith("f"))
11599  ABIFLen = 32;
11600  else if (ABIStr.endswith("d"))
11601  ABIFLen = 64;
11602  return SetCGInfo(new RISCVTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, XLen, ABIFLen));
11603  }
11604 
11605  case llvm::Triple::systemz: {
11606  bool SoftFloat = CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft";
11607  bool HasVector = !SoftFloat && getTarget().getABI() == "vector";
11608  return SetCGInfo(new SystemZTargetCodeGenInfo(Types, HasVector, SoftFloat));
11609  }
11610 
11611  case llvm::Triple::tce:
11612  case llvm::Triple::tcele:
11613  return SetCGInfo(new TCETargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11614 
11615  case llvm::Triple::x86: {
11616  bool IsDarwinVectorABI = Triple.isOSDarwin();
11617  bool RetSmallStructInRegABI =
11618  X86_32TargetCodeGenInfo::isStructReturnInRegABI(Triple, CodeGenOpts);
11619  bool IsWin32FloatStructABI = Triple.isOSWindows() && !Triple.isOSCygMing();
11620 
11621  if (Triple.getOS() == llvm::Triple::Win32) {
11622  return SetCGInfo(new WinX86_32TargetCodeGenInfo(
11623  Types, IsDarwinVectorABI, RetSmallStructInRegABI,
11624  IsWin32FloatStructABI, CodeGenOpts.NumRegisterParameters));
11625  } else {
11626  return SetCGInfo(new X86_32TargetCodeGenInfo(
11627  Types, IsDarwinVectorABI, RetSmallStructInRegABI,
11628  IsWin32FloatStructABI, CodeGenOpts.NumRegisterParameters,
11629  CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft"));
11630  }
11631  }
11632 
11633  case llvm::Triple::x86_64: {
11634  StringRef ABI = getTarget().getABI();
11635  X86AVXABILevel AVXLevel =
11636  (ABI == "avx512"
11637  ? X86AVXABILevel::AVX512
11638  : ABI == "avx" ? X86AVXABILevel::AVX : X86AVXABILevel::None);
11639 
11640  switch (Triple.getOS()) {
11641  case llvm::Triple::Win32:
11642  return SetCGInfo(new WinX86_64TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, AVXLevel));
11643  default:
11644  return SetCGInfo(new X86_64TargetCodeGenInfo(Types, AVXLevel));
11645  }
11646  }
11647  case llvm::Triple::hexagon:
11648  return SetCGInfo(new HexagonTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11649  case llvm::Triple::lanai:
11650  return SetCGInfo(new LanaiTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11651  case llvm::Triple::r600:
11652  return SetCGInfo(new AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11653  case llvm::Triple::amdgcn:
11654  return SetCGInfo(new AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11655  case llvm::Triple::sparc:
11656  return SetCGInfo(new SparcV8TargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11657  case llvm::Triple::sparcv9:
11658  return SetCGInfo(new SparcV9TargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11659  case llvm::Triple::xcore:
11660  return SetCGInfo(new XCoreTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11661  case llvm::Triple::arc:
11662  return SetCGInfo(new ARCTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11663  case llvm::Triple::spir:
11664  case llvm::Triple::spir64:
11665  return SetCGInfo(new CommonSPIRTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11666  case llvm::Triple::spirv32:
11667  case llvm::Triple::spirv64:
11668  return SetCGInfo(new SPIRVTargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11669  case llvm::Triple::ve:
11670  return SetCGInfo(new VETargetCodeGenInfo(Types));
11671  }
11672 }
11673 
11674 /// Create an OpenCL kernel for an enqueued block.
11675 ///
11676 /// The kernel has the same function type as the block invoke function. Its
11677 /// name is the name of the block invoke function postfixed with "_kernel".
11678 /// It simply calls the block invoke function then returns.
11679 llvm::Function *
11680 TargetCodeGenInfo::createEnqueuedBlockKernel(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
11681  llvm::Function *Invoke,
11682  llvm::Type *BlockTy) const {
11683  auto *InvokeFT = Invoke->getFunctionType();
11684  auto &C = CGF.getLLVMContext();
11685  std::string Name = Invoke->getName().str() + "_kernel";
11686  auto *FT = llvm::FunctionType::get(llvm::Type::getVoidTy(C),
11687  InvokeFT->params(), false);
11688  auto *F = llvm::Function::Create(FT, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, Name,
11689  &CGF.CGM.getModule());
11690  auto IP = CGF.Builder.saveIP();
11691  auto *BB = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(C, "entry", F);
11692  auto &Builder = CGF.Builder;
11693  Builder.SetInsertPoint(BB);
11694  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 2> Args(llvm::make_pointer_range(F->args()));
11695  llvm::CallInst *call = Builder.CreateCall(Invoke, Args);
11696  call->setCallingConv(Invoke->getCallingConv());
11697  Builder.CreateRetVoid();
11698  Builder.restoreIP(IP);
11699  return F;
11700 }
11701 
11702 /// Create an OpenCL kernel for an enqueued block.
11703 ///
11704 /// The type of the first argument (the block literal) is the struct type
11705 /// of the block literal instead of a pointer type. The first argument
11706 /// (block literal) is passed directly by value to the kernel. The kernel
11707 /// allocates the same type of struct on stack and stores the block literal
11708 /// to it and passes its pointer to the block invoke function. The kernel
11709 /// has "enqueued-block" function attribute and kernel argument metadata.
11710 llvm::Function *AMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo::createEnqueuedBlockKernel(
11711  CodeGenFunction &CGF, llvm::Function *Invoke,
11712  llvm::Type *BlockTy) const {
11713  auto &Builder = CGF.Builder;
11714  auto &C = CGF.getLLVMContext();
11715 
11716  auto *InvokeFT = Invoke->getFunctionType();
11717  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Type *, 2> ArgTys;
11718  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> AddressQuals;
11719  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> AccessQuals;
11720  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> ArgTypeNames;
11721  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> ArgBaseTypeNames;
11722  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> ArgTypeQuals;
11723  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> ArgNames;
11724 
11725  ArgTys.push_back(BlockTy);
11726  ArgTypeNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "__block_literal"));
11727  AddressQuals.push_back(llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(Builder.getInt32(0)));
11728  ArgBaseTypeNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "__block_literal"));
11729  ArgTypeQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, ""));
11730  AccessQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "none"));
11731  ArgNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "block_literal"));
11732  for (unsigned I = 1, E = InvokeFT->getNumParams(); I < E; ++I) {
11733  ArgTys.push_back(InvokeFT->getParamType(I));
11734  ArgTypeNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "void*"));
11735  AddressQuals.push_back(llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(Builder.getInt32(3)));
11736  AccessQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "none"));
11737  ArgBaseTypeNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, "void*"));
11738  ArgTypeQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(C, ""));
11739  ArgNames.push_back(
11740  llvm::MDString::get(C, (Twine("local_arg") + Twine(I)).str()));
11741  }
11742  std::string Name = Invoke->getName().str() + "_kernel";
11743  auto *FT = llvm::FunctionType::get(llvm::Type::getVoidTy(C), ArgTys, false);
11744  auto *F = llvm::Function::Create(FT, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, Name,
11745  &CGF.CGM.getModule());
11746  F->addFnAttr("enqueued-block");
11747  auto IP = CGF.Builder.saveIP();
11748  auto *BB = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(C, "entry", F);
11749  Builder.SetInsertPoint(BB);
11750  const auto BlockAlign = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getPrefTypeAlign(BlockTy);
11751  auto *BlockPtr = Builder.CreateAlloca(BlockTy, nullptr);
11752  BlockPtr->setAlignment(BlockAlign);
11753  Builder.CreateAlignedStore(F->arg_begin(), BlockPtr, BlockAlign);
11754  auto *Cast = Builder.CreatePointerCast(BlockPtr, InvokeFT->getParamType(0));
11755  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Value *, 2> Args;
11756  Args.push_back(Cast);
11757  for (auto I = F->arg_begin() + 1, E = F->arg_end(); I != E; ++I)
11758  Args.push_back(I);
11759  llvm::CallInst *call = Builder.CreateCall(Invoke, Args);
11760  call->setCallingConv(Invoke->getCallingConv());
11761  Builder.CreateRetVoid();
11762  Builder.restoreIP(IP);
11763 
11764  F->setMetadata("kernel_arg_addr_space", llvm::MDNode::get(C, AddressQuals));
11765  F->setMetadata("kernel_arg_access_qual", llvm::MDNode::get(C, AccessQuals));
11766  F->setMetadata("kernel_arg_type", llvm::MDNode::get(C, ArgTypeNames));
11767  F->setMetadata("kernel_arg_base_type",
11768  llvm::MDNode::get(C, ArgBaseTypeNames));
11769  F->setMetadata("kernel_arg_type_qual", llvm::MDNode::get(C, ArgTypeQuals));
11770  if (CGF.CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmitOpenCLArgMetadata)
11771  F->setMetadata("kernel_arg_name", llvm::MDNode::get(C, ArgNames));
11772 
11773  return F;
11774 }
